var book = {
	"name": "1 Samuel",
	"numChapters": 31,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>Now there was a certain man from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7214A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7214A\"></sup>Ramathaim-zophim from the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7214B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7214B\"></sup>hill country of Ephraim, and his name was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7214C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7214C\"></sup>Elkanah the son of Jeroham, the son of Elihu, the son of Tohu, the son of Zuph, an Ephraimite.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7215D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7215D\"></sup>two wives: the name of one was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7215E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7215E\"></sup>Hannah and the name of the other Peninnah; and Peninnah had children, but Hannah had no children.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now this man would go up from his city <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7216F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7216F\"></sup>yearly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7216G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7216G\"></sup>to worship and to sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of hosts in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7216H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7216H\"></sup>Shiloh. And the two sons of Eli, Hophni and Phinehas, were priests to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> there.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When the day came that Elkanah sacrificed, he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7217I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7217I\"></sup>would give portions to Peninnah his wife and to all her sons and her daughters;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>but to Hannah he would give a double portion, for he loved Hannah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7218J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7218J\"></sup>but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had closed her womb.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Her rival, however, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7219K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7219K\"></sup>would provoke her bitterly to irritate her, because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had closed her womb.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>It happened year after year, as often as she went up to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, she would provoke her; so she wept and would not eat.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Elkanah her husband said to her, “Hannah, why do you weep and why do you not eat and why is your heart sad? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7221L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7221L\"></sup>Am I not better to you than ten sons?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Hannah rose after eating and drinking in Shiloh. Now Eli the priest was sitting on the seat by the doorpost of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7222M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7222M\"></sup>the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>She, greatly distressed, prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and wept bitterly.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>She <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7224N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7224N\"></sup>made a vow and said, “O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of hosts, if You will indeed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7224O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7224O\"></sup>look on the affliction of Your maidservant and remember me, and not forget Your maidservant, but will give Your maidservant a son, then I will give him to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> all the days of his life, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7224P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7224P\"></sup>a razor shall never come on his head.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now it came about, as she continued praying before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, that Eli was watching her mouth.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>As for Hannah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7226Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7226Q\"></sup>she was speaking in her heart, only her lips were moving, but her voice was not heard. So Eli thought she was drunk.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then Eli said to her, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7227R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7227R\"></sup>How long will you make yourself drunk? Put away your wine from you.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But Hannah replied, “No, my lord, I am a woman oppressed in spirit; I have drunk neither wine nor strong drink, but I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7228S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7228S\"></sup>have poured out my soul before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Do not consider your maidservant as a worthless woman, for I have spoken until now out of my great concern and provocation.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Eli answered and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7230T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7230T\"></sup>Go in peace; and may the God of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7230U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7230U\"></sup>grant your petition that you have asked of Him.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>She said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7231V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7231V\"></sup>Let your maidservant find favor in your sight.” So the woman went her way and ate, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7231W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7231W\"></sup>her face was no longer <i>sad</i>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then they arose early in the morning and worshiped before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and returned again to their house in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7232X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7232X\"></sup>Ramah. And Elkanah had relations with Hannah his wife, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7232Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7232Y\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> remembered her.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>It came about in due time, after Hannah had conceived, that she gave birth to a son; and she named him Samuel, <i>saying</i>, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7233Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7233Z\"></sup>Because I have asked him of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then the man Elkanah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7234AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7234AA\"></sup>went up with all his household to offer to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> the yearly sacrifice and <i>pay</i> his vow.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But Hannah did not go up, for she said to her husband, “<i>I will not go up</i> until the child is weaned; then I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7235AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7235AB\"></sup>bring him, that he may appear before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7235AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7235AC\"></sup>stay there forever.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7236AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7236AD\"></sup>Elkanah her husband said to her, “Do what seems best to you. Remain until you have weaned him; only <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7236AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7236AE\"></sup>may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> confirm His word.” So the woman remained and nursed her son until she weaned him.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Now when she had weaned him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7237AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7237AF\"></sup>she took him up with her, with a three-year-old bull and one ephah of flour and a jug of wine, and brought him to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7237AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7237AG\"></sup>the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in Shiloh, although the child was young.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7238AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7238AH\"></sup>they slaughtered the bull, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7238AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7238AI\"></sup>brought the boy to Eli.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>She said, “Oh, my lord! <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7239AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7239AJ\"></sup>As your soul lives, my lord, I am the woman who stood here beside you, praying to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7240AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7240AK\"></sup>For this boy I prayed, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given me my petition which I asked of Him.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7241AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7241AL\"></sup>So I have also dedicated him to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; as long as he lives he is dedicated to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7241AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7241AM\"></sup>he worshiped the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> there."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>Then Hannah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7242A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7242A\"></sup>prayed and said,“My heart exults in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7242B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7242B\"></sup>My horn is exalted in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,My mouth speaks boldly against my enemies,Because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7242C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7242C\"></sup>I rejoice in Your salvation.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7243D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7243D\"></sup>There is no one holy like the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,Indeed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7243E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7243E\"></sup>there is no one besides You,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7243F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7243F\"></sup>Nor is there any rock like our God.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“Boast no more so very proudly,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7244G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7244G\"></sup>Do not let arrogance come out of your mouth;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7244H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7244H\"></sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is a God of knowledge,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7244I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7244I\"></sup>And with Him actions are weighed.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7245J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7245J\"></sup>The bows of the mighty are shattered,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7245K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7245K\"></sup>But the feeble gird on strength.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“Those who were full hire themselves out for bread,But those who were hungry cease <i>to hunger</i>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7246L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7246L\"></sup>Even the barren gives birth to seven,But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7246M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7246M\"></sup>she who has many children languishes.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7247N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7247N\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> kills and makes alive;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7247O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7247O\"></sup>He brings down to Sheol and raises up.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7248P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7248P\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> makes poor and rich;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7248Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7248Q\"></sup>He brings low, He also exalts.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7249R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7249R\"></sup>He raises the poor from the dust,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7249S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7249S\"></sup>He lifts the needy from the ash heap<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7249T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7249T\"></sup>To make them sit with nobles,And inherit a seat of honor;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7249U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7249U\"></sup>For the pillars of the earth are the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span>,And He set the world on them.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7250V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7250V\"></sup>He keeps the feet of His godly ones,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7250W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7250W\"></sup>But the wicked ones are silenced in darkness;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7250X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7250X\"></sup>For not by might shall a man prevail.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7251Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7251Y\"></sup>Those who contend with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will be shattered;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7251Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7251Z\"></sup>Against them He will thunder in the heavens,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7251AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7251AA\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will judge the ends of the earth;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7251AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7251AB\"></sup>And He will give strength to His king,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7251AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7251AC\"></sup>And will exalt the horn of His anointed.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then Elkanah went to his home at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7252AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7252AD\"></sup>Ramah. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7252AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7252AE\"></sup>But the boy ministered to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> before Eli the priest.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now the sons of Eli were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7253AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7253AF\"></sup>worthless men; they did not know the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7254AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7254AG\"></sup>and the custom of the priests with the people. When any man was offering a sacrifice, the priest’s servant would come while the meat was boiling, with a three-pronged fork in his hand.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then he would thrust it into the pan, or kettle, or caldron, or pot; all that the fork brought up the priest would take for himself. Thus they did in Shiloh to all the Israelites who came there.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Also, before <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7256AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7256AH\"></sup>they burned the fat, the priest’s servant would come and say to the man who was sacrificing, “Give the priest meat for roasting, as he will not take boiled meat from you, only raw.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>If the man said to him, “They must surely burn the fat first, and then take as much as you desire,” then he would say, “No, but you shall give <i>it to me</i> now; and if not, I will take it by force.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Thus the sin of the young men was very great before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for the men <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7258AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7258AI\"></sup>despised the offering of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7259AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7259AJ\"></sup>Samuel was ministering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <i>as</i> a boy <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7259AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7259AK\"></sup>wearing a linen ephod.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And his mother would make him a little <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7260AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7260AL\"></sup>robe and bring it to him from year to year when she would come up with her husband to offer <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7260AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7260AM\"></sup>the yearly sacrifice.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Eli would <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7261AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7261AN\"></sup>bless Elkanah and his wife and say, “May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> give you children from this woman in place of the one she <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7261AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7261AO\"></sup>dedicated to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” And they went to their own home.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7262AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7262AP\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> visited Hannah; and she conceived and gave birth to three sons and two daughters. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7262AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7262AQ\"></sup>the boy Samuel grew before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Now Eli was very old; and he heard <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7263AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7263AR\"></sup>all that his sons were doing to all Israel, and how they lay with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7263AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7263AS\"></sup>the women who served at the doorway of the tent of meeting.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He said to them, “Why do you do such things, the evil things that I hear from all these people?",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>No, my sons; for the report is not good <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7265AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7265AT\"></sup>which I hear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> people circulating.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>If one man sins against another, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7266AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7266AU\"></sup>God will mediate for him; but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7266AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7266AV\"></sup>if a man sins against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who can intercede for him?” But they would not listen to the voice of their father, for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7266AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7266AW\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> desired to put them to death.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Now the boy <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7267AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7267AX\"></sup>Samuel was growing in stature and in favor both with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and with men.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7268AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7268AY\"></sup>a man of God came to Eli and said to him, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7268AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7268AZ\"></sup>Did I <i>not</i> indeed reveal Myself to the house of your father when they were in Egypt <i>in bondage</i> to Pharaoh’s house?",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7269BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7269BA\"></sup>Did I <i>not</i> choose them from all the tribes of Israel to be My priests, to go up to My altar, to burn incense, to carry an ephod before Me; and did I <i>not</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7269BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7269BB\"></sup>give to the house of your father all the fire <i>offerings</i> of the sons of Israel?",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Why do you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7270BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7270BC\"></sup>kick at My sacrifice and at My offering <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7270BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7270BD\"></sup>which I have commanded <i>in My</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7270BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7270BE\"></sup>dwelling, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7270BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7270BF\"></sup>honor your sons above Me, by making yourselves fat with the choicest of every offering of My people Israel?’",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel declares, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7271BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7271BG\"></sup>I did indeed say that your house and the house of your father should walk before Me forever’; but now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> declares, ‘Far be it from Me—for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7271BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7271BH\"></sup>those who honor Me I will honor, and those <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7271BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7271BI\"></sup>who despise Me will be lightly esteemed.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7272BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7272BJ\"></sup>the days are coming when I will break your strength and the strength of your father’s house so that there will not be an old man in your house.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>You will see <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7273BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7273BK\"></sup>the distress of <i>My</i> dwelling, in <i>spite of</i> all the good that I do for Israel; and an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7273BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7273BL\"></sup>old man will not be in your house forever.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Yet I will not cut off every man of yours from My altar so that your eyes will fail <i>from weeping</i> and your soul grieve, and all the increase of your house will die in the prime of life.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>This will be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7275BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7275BM\"></sup>the sign to you which will come concerning your two sons, Hophni and Phinehas: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7275BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7275BN\"></sup>on the same day both of them will die.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7276BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7276BO\"></sup>I will raise up for Myself a faithful priest who will do according to what is in My heart and in My soul; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7276BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7276BP\"></sup>I will build him an enduring house, and he will walk before <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7276BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7276BQ\"></sup>My anointed always.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Everyone who is left in your house will come and bow down to him for a piece of silver or a loaf of bread and say, “Please assign me to one of the priest’s offices so that I may eat a piece of bread.”’”"
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7278A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7278A\"></sup>the boy Samuel was ministering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> before Eli. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7278B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7278B\"></sup>word from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was rare in those days, visions were infrequent.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>It happened at that time as Eli was lying down in his place (now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7279C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7279C\"></sup>his eyesight had begun to grow dim <i>and</i> he could not see <i>well</i>),",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7280D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7280D\"></sup>the lamp of God had not yet gone out, and Samuel was lying down in the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> where the ark of God <i>was</i>,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> called Samuel; and he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7281E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7281E\"></sup>Here I am.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then he ran to Eli and said, “Here I am, for you called me.” But he said, “I did not call, lie down again.” So he went and lay down.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> called yet again, “Samuel!” So Samuel arose and went to Eli and said, “Here I am, for you called me.” But he answered, “I did not call, my son, lie down again.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7284F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7284F\"></sup>Now Samuel did not yet know the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, nor had the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> yet been revealed to him.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> called Samuel again for the third time. And he arose and went to Eli and said, “Here I am, for you called me.” Then Eli discerned that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was calling the boy.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Eli said to Samuel, “Go lie down, and it shall be if He calls you, that you shall say, ‘Speak, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for Your servant is listening.’” So Samuel went and lay down in his place.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came and stood and called as at other times, “Samuel! Samuel!” And Samuel said, “Speak, for Your servant is listening.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Samuel, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7288G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7288G\"></sup>I am about to do a thing in Israel at which both ears of everyone who hears it will tingle.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>In that day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7289H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7289H\"></sup>I will carry out against Eli all that I have spoken concerning his house, from beginning to end.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7290I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7290I\"></sup>I have told him that I am about to judge his house forever for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7290J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7290J\"></sup>the iniquity which he knew, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7290K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7290K\"></sup>his sons brought a curse on themselves and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7290L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7290L\"></sup>he did not rebuke them.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Therefore I have sworn to the house of Eli that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7291M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7291M\"></sup>the iniquity of Eli’s house shall not be atoned for by sacrifice or offering forever.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So Samuel lay down until morning. Then he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7292N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7292N\"></sup>opened the doors of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. But Samuel was afraid to tell <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7292O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7292O\"></sup>the vision to Eli.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Eli called Samuel and said, “Samuel, my son.” And he said, “Here I am.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He said, “What is the word that He spoke to you? Please do not hide it from me. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7294P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7294P\"></sup>May God do so to you, and more also, if you hide anything from me of all the words that He spoke to you.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So Samuel told him everything and hid nothing from him. And he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7295Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7295Q\"></sup>It is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; let Him do what seems good to Him.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Thus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7296R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7296R\"></sup>Samuel grew and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7296S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7296S\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7296T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7296T\"></sup>let none of his words fail.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>All Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7297U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7297U\"></sup>from Dan even to Beersheba knew that Samuel was confirmed as a prophet of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7298V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7298V\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared again at Shiloh, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7298W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7298W\"></sup>because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> revealed Himself to Samuel at Shiloh by the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>Thus the word of Samuel came to all Israel. Now Israel went out to meet the Philistines in battle and camped beside <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7299A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7299A\"></sup>Ebenezer while the Philistines camped in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7299B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7299B\"></sup>Aphek.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The Philistines drew up in battle array to meet Israel. When the battle spread, Israel was defeated before the Philistines who killed about four thousand men on the battlefield.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When the people came into the camp, the elders of Israel said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7301C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7301C\"></sup>Why has the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> defeated us today before the Philistines? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7301D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7301D\"></sup>Let us take to ourselves from Shiloh the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, that it may come among us and deliver us from the power of our enemies.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So the people sent to Shiloh, and from there they carried the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of hosts <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7302E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7302E\"></sup>who sits <i>above</i> the cherubim; and the two sons of Eli, Hophni and Phinehas, <i>were</i> there with the ark of the covenant of God.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>As the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came into the camp, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7303F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7303F\"></sup>all Israel shouted with a great shout, so that the earth resounded.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When the Philistines heard the noise of the shout, they said, “What <i>does</i> the noise of this great shout in the camp of the Hebrews <i>mean</i>?” Then they understood that the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had come into the camp.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The Philistines were afraid, for they said, “God has come into the camp.” And they said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7305G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7305G\"></sup>Woe to us! For nothing like this has happened before.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Woe to us! Who shall deliver us from the hand of these mighty gods? These are the gods who smote the Egyptians with all <i>kinds of</i> plagues in the wilderness.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7307H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7307H\"></sup>Take courage and be men, O Philistines, or you will become slaves to the Hebrews, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7307I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7307I\"></sup>as they have been slaves to you; therefore, be men and fight.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So the Philistines fought and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7308J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7308J\"></sup>Israel was defeated, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7308K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7308K\"></sup>every man fled to his tent; and the slaughter was very great, for there fell of Israel thirty thousand foot soldiers.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And the ark of God was taken; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7309L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7309L\"></sup>the two sons of Eli, Hophni and Phinehas, died.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now a man of Benjamin ran from the battle line and came to Shiloh the same day with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7310M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7310M\"></sup>his clothes torn and dust on his head.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When he came, behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7311N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7311N\"></sup>Eli was sitting on <i>his</i> seat by the road eagerly watching, because his heart was trembling for the ark of God. So the man came to tell <i>it</i> in the city, and all the city cried out.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When Eli heard the noise of the outcry, he said, “What <i>does</i> the noise of this commotion <i>mean</i>?” Then the man came hurriedly and told Eli.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now Eli was ninety-eight years old, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7313O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7313O\"></sup>his eyes were set so that he could not see.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The man said to Eli, “I am the one who came from the battle line. Indeed, I escaped from the battle line today.” And he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7314P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7314P\"></sup>How did things go, my son?”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then the one who brought the news replied, “Israel has fled before the Philistines and there has also been a great slaughter among the people, and your two sons also, Hophni and Phinehas, are dead, and the ark of God has been taken.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When he mentioned the ark of God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7316Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7316Q\"></sup>Eli fell off the seat backward beside the gate, and his neck was broken and he died, for he was old and heavy. Thus he judged Israel forty years.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now his daughter-in-law, Phinehas’s wife, was pregnant and about to give birth; and when she heard the news that the ark of God was taken and that her father-in-law and her husband had died, she kneeled down and gave birth, for her pains came upon her.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And about the time of her death the women who stood by her said to her, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7318R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7318R\"></sup>Do not be afraid, for you have given birth to a son.” But she did not answer or pay attention.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And she called the boy Ichabod, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7319S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7319S\"></sup>The glory has departed from Israel,” because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7319T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7319T\"></sup>the ark of God was taken and because of her father-in-law and her husband.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>She said, “The glory has departed from Israel, for the ark of God was taken.”"
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>Now the Philistines took the ark of God and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7321A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7321A\"></sup>brought it from Ebenezer to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7321B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7321B\"></sup>Ashdod.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then the Philistines took the ark of God and brought it to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7322C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7322C\"></sup>the house of Dagon and set it by Dagon.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When the Ashdodites arose early the next morning, behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7323D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7323D\"></sup>Dagon had fallen on his face to the ground before the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. So they took Dagon and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7323E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7323E\"></sup>set him in his place again.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But when they arose early the next morning, behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7324F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7324F\"></sup>Dagon had fallen on his face to the ground before the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. And the head of Dagon and both the palms of his hands <i>were</i> cut off on the threshold; only the trunk of Dagon was left to him.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Therefore neither the priests of Dagon nor all who enter Dagon’s house <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7325G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7325G\"></sup>tread on the threshold of Dagon in Ashdod to this day.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7326H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7326H\"></sup>the hand of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was heavy on the Ashdodites, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7326I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7326I\"></sup>He ravaged them and smote them with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7326J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7326J\"></sup>tumors, both Ashdod and its territories.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When the men of Ashdod saw that it was so, they said, “The ark of the God of Israel must not remain with us, for His hand is severe on us and on Dagon our god.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So they sent and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7328K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7328K\"></sup>gathered all the lords of the Philistines to them and said, “What shall we do with the ark of the God of Israel?” And they said, “Let the ark of the God of Israel be brought around to Gath.” And they brought the ark of the God of Israel <i>around</i>.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>After they had brought it around, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7329L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7329L\"></sup>the hand of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was against the city with very great confusion; and He smote the men of the city, both young and old, so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7329M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7329M\"></sup>tumors broke out on them.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So they sent the ark of God to Ekron. And as the ark of God came to Ekron the Ekronites cried out, saying, “They have brought the ark of the God of Israel around to us, to kill us and our people.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>They <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7331N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7331N\"></sup>sent therefore and gathered all the lords of the Philistines and said, “Send away the ark of the God of Israel, and let it return to its own place, so that it will not kill us and our people.” For there was a deadly confusion throughout the city; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7331O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7331O\"></sup>the hand of God was very heavy there.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And the men who did not die were smitten with tumors and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7332P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7332P\"></sup>the cry of the city went up to heaven."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>Now the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had been in the country of the Philistines seven months.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7334A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7334A\"></sup>the Philistines called for the priests and the diviners, saying, “What shall we do with the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>? Tell us how we shall send it to its place.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They said, “If you send away the ark of the God of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7335B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7335B\"></sup>do not send it empty; but you shall surely <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7335C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7335C\"></sup>return to Him a guilt offering. Then you will be healed and it will be known to you why His hand is not removed from you.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then they said, “What shall be the guilt offering which we shall return to Him?” And they said, “Five golden <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7336D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7336D\"></sup>tumors and five golden mice <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7336E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7336E\"></sup><i>according to</i> the number of the lords of the Philistines, for one plague was on all of you and on your lords.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So you shall make likenesses of your tumors and likenesses of your mice that ravage the land, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7337F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7337F\"></sup>you shall give glory to the God of Israel; perhaps <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7337G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7337G\"></sup>He will ease His hand from you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7337H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7337H\"></sup>your gods, and your land.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Why then do you harden your hearts <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7338I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7338I\"></sup>as the Egyptians and Pharaoh hardened their hearts? When He had severely dealt with them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7338J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7338J\"></sup>did they not allow the people to go, and they departed?",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now therefore, take and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7339K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7339K\"></sup>prepare a new cart and two milch cows on which there <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7339L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7339L\"></sup>has never been a yoke; and hitch the cows to the cart and take their calves home, away from them.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Take the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and place it on the cart; and put <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7340M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7340M\"></sup>the articles of gold which you return to Him as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7340N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7340N\"></sup>a guilt offering in a box by its side. Then send it away that it may go.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Watch, if it goes up by the way of its own territory to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7341O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7341O\"></sup>Beth-shemesh, then He has done us this great evil. But if not, then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7341P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7341P\"></sup>we will know that it was not His hand that struck us; it happened to us by chance.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then the men did so, and took two milch cows and hitched them to the cart, and shut up their calves at home.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>They put the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on the cart, and the box with the golden mice and the likenesses of their tumors.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And the cows took the straight way in the direction of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7344Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7344Q\"></sup>Beth-shemesh; they went along <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7344R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7344R\"></sup>the highway, lowing as they went, and did not turn aside to the right or to the left. And the lords of the Philistines followed them to the border of Beth-shemesh.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now <i>the people of</i> Beth-shemesh were reaping their wheat harvest in the valley, and they raised their eyes and saw the ark and were glad to see <i>it</i>.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The cart came into the field of Joshua the Beth-shemite and stood there where there <i>was</i> a large stone; and they split the wood of the cart and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7346S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7346S\"></sup>offered the cows as a burnt offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7347T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7347T\"></sup>The Levites took down the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the box that was with it, in which were the articles of gold, and put them on the large stone; and the men of Beth-shemesh offered burnt offerings and sacrificed sacrifices that day to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7348U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7348U\"></sup>five lords of the Philistines saw it, they returned to Ekron that day.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7349V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7349V\"></sup>These are the golden tumors which the Philistines returned for a guilt offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: one for Ashdod, one for Gaza, one for Ashkelon, one for Gath, one for Ekron;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and the golden mice, <i>according</i> to the number of all the cities of the Philistines belonging to the five lords, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7350W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7350W\"></sup>both of fortified cities and of country villages. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7350X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7350X\"></sup>The large stone on which they set the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <i>is a witness</i> to this day in the field of Joshua the Beth-shemite.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7351Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7351Y\"></sup>He struck down some of the men of Beth-shemesh because they had looked into the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. He struck down of all the people, 50,070 men, and the people mourned because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had struck the people with a great slaughter.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The men of Beth-shemesh said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7352Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7352Z\"></sup>Who is able to stand before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, this holy God? And to whom shall He go up from us?”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So they sent messengers to the inhabitants of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7353AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7353AA\"></sup>Kiriath-jearim, saying, “The Philistines have brought back the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; come down and take it up to you.”"
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>And the men of Kiriath-jearim came and took the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7354A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7354A\"></sup>brought it into the house of Abinadab on the hill, and consecrated Eleazar his son to keep the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>From the day that the ark remained at Kiriath-jearim, the time was long, for it was twenty years; and all the house of Israel lamented after the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then Samuel spoke to all the house of Israel, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7356B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7356B\"></sup>If you return to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with all your heart, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7356C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7356C\"></sup>remove the foreign gods and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7356D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7356D\"></sup>Ashtaroth from among you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7356E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7356E\"></sup>direct your hearts to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7356F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7356F\"></sup>serve Him alone; and He will deliver you from the hand of the Philistines.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So the sons of Israel removed the Baals and the Ashtaroth and served the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> alone.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Samuel said, “Gather all Israel to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7358G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7358G\"></sup>Mizpah and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7358H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7358H\"></sup>I will pray to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for you.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They gathered to Mizpah, and drew water and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7359I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7359I\"></sup>poured it out before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7359J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7359J\"></sup>fasted on that day and said there, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7359K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7359K\"></sup>We have sinned against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” And Samuel judged the sons of Israel at Mizpah.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now when the Philistines heard that the sons of Israel had gathered to Mizpah, the lords of the Philistines went up against Israel. And when the sons of Israel heard it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7360L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7360L\"></sup>they were afraid of the Philistines.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then the sons of Israel said to Samuel, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7361M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7361M\"></sup>Do not cease to cry to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God for us, that He may save us from the hand of the Philistines.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Samuel took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7362N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7362N\"></sup>a suckling lamb and offered it for a whole burnt offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; and Samuel cried to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for Israel and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7362O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7362O\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> answered him.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now Samuel was offering up the burnt offering, and the Philistines drew near to battle against Israel. But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7363P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7363P\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> thundered with a great thunder on that day against the Philistines and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7363Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7363Q\"></sup>confused them, so that they were routed before Israel.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The men of Israel went out of Mizpah and pursued the Philistines, and struck them down as far as below Beth-car.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Samuel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7365R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7365R\"></sup>took a stone and set it between Mizpah and Shen, and named it Ebenezer, saying, “Thus far the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has helped us.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7366S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7366S\"></sup>So the Philistines were subdued and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7366T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7366T\"></sup>they did not come anymore within the border of Israel. And the hand of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was against the Philistines all the days of Samuel.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The cities which the Philistines had taken from Israel were restored to Israel, from Ekron even to Gath; and Israel delivered their territory from the hand of the Philistines. So there was peace between Israel and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7367U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7367U\"></sup>the Amorites.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now Samuel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7368V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7368V\"></sup>judged Israel all the days of his life.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He used to go annually on circuit to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7369W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7369W\"></sup>Bethel and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7369X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7369X\"></sup>Gilgal and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7369Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7369Y\"></sup>Mizpah, and he judged Israel in all these places.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then his return <i>was</i> to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7370Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7370Z\"></sup>Ramah, for his house <i>was</i> there, and there he judged Israel; and he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7370AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7370AA\"></sup>built there an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>And it came about when Samuel was old that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7371A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7371A\"></sup>he appointed his sons judges over Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Now the name of his firstborn was Joel, and the name of his second, Abijah; <i>they</i> were judging in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7372B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7372B\"></sup>Beersheba.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>His sons, however, did not walk in his ways, but turned aside after dishonest gain and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7373C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7373C\"></sup>took bribes and perverted justice.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then all the elders of Israel gathered together and came to Samuel at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7374D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7374D\"></sup>Ramah;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and they said to him, “Behold, you have grown old, and your sons do not walk in your ways. Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7375E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7375E\"></sup>appoint a king for us to judge us like all the nations.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But the thing was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7376F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7376F\"></sup>displeasing in the sight of Samuel when they said, “Give us a king to judge us.” And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7376G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7376G\"></sup>Samuel prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Samuel, “Listen to the voice of the people in regard to all that they say to you, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7377H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7377H\"></sup>they have not rejected you, but they have rejected Me from being king over them.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Like all the deeds which they have done since the day that I brought them up from Egypt even to this day—in that they have forsaken Me and served other gods—so they are doing to you also.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now then, listen to their voice; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7379I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7379I\"></sup>however, you shall solemnly warn them and tell them of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7379J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7379J\"></sup>the procedure of the king who will reign over them.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So Samuel spoke all the words of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7380K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7380K\"></sup>the people who had asked of him a king.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7381L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7381L\"></sup>This will be the procedure of the king who will reign over you: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7381M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7381M\"></sup>he will take your sons and place <i>them</i> for himself in his chariots and among his horsemen and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7381N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7381N\"></sup>they will run before his chariots.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7382O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7382O\"></sup>He will appoint for himself commanders of thousands and of fifties, and <i>some</i> to do his plowing and to reap his harvest and to make his weapons of war and equipment for his chariots.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He will also take your daughters for perfumers and cooks and bakers.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7384P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7384P\"></sup>He will take the best of your fields and your vineyards and your olive groves and give <i>them</i> to his servants.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He will take a tenth of your seed and of your vineyards and give to his officers and to his servants.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He will also take your male servants and your female servants and your best young men and your donkeys and use <i>them</i> for his work.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He will take a tenth of your flocks, and you yourselves will become his servants.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7388Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7388Q\"></sup>you will cry out in that day because of your king whom you have chosen for yourselves, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7388R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7388R\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will not answer you in that day.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Nevertheless, the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7389S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7389S\"></sup>refused to listen to the voice of Samuel, and they said, “No, but there shall be a king over us,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7390T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7390T\"></sup>that we also may be like all the nations, that our king may judge us and go out before us and fight our battles.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Now after Samuel had heard all the words of the people, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7391U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7391U\"></sup>he repeated them in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> hearing.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Samuel, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7392V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7392V\"></sup>Listen to their voice and appoint them a king.” So Samuel said to the men of Israel, “Go every man to his city.”"
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>Now there was a man of Benjamin whose name was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7393A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7393A\"></sup>Kish the son of Abiel, the son of Zeror, the son of Becorath, the son of Aphiah, the son of a Benjamite, a mighty man of valor.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He had a son whose name was Saul, a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7394B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7394B\"></sup>choice and handsome <i>man</i>, and there was not a more handsome person than he among the sons of Israel; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7394C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7394C\"></sup>from his shoulders and up he was taller than any of the people.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now the donkeys of Kish, Saul’s father, were lost. So Kish said to his son Saul, “Take now with you one of the servants, and arise, go search for the donkeys.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He passed through <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7396D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7396D\"></sup>the hill country of Ephraim and passed through the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7396E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7396E\"></sup>Shalishah, but they did not find <i>them</i>. Then they passed through the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7396F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7396F\"></sup>Shaalim, but <i>they were</i> not <i>there</i>. Then he passed through the land of the Benjamites, but they did not find <i>them</i>.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When they came to the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7397G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7397G\"></sup>Zuph, Saul said to his servant who was with him, “Come, and let us return, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7397H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7397H\"></sup>or else my father will cease <i>to be concerned</i> about the donkeys and will become anxious for us.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He said to him, “Behold now, there is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7398I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7398I\"></sup>a man of God in this city, and the man is held in honor; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7398J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7398J\"></sup>all that he says surely comes true. Now let us go there, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7398K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7398K\"></sup>perhaps he can tell us about our journey on which we have set out.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then Saul said to his servant, “But behold, if we go, what shall we bring the man? For the bread is gone from our sack and there is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7399L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7399L\"></sup>no present to bring to the man of God. What do we have?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The servant answered Saul again and said, “Behold, I have in my hand a fourth of a shekel of silver; I will give <i>it</i> to the man of God and he will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7400M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7400M\"></sup>tell us our way.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>(Formerly in Israel, when a man went to inquire of God, he used to say, “Come, and let us go to the seer”; for <i>he who is called</i> a prophet now was formerly called <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7401N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7401N\"></sup>a seer.)",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Saul said to his servant, “Well said; come, let us go.” So they went to the city where the man of God was.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>As they went up the slope to the city, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7403O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7403O\"></sup>they found young women going out to draw water and said to them, “Is the seer here?”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They answered them and said, “He is; see, <i>he is</i> ahead of you. Hurry now, for he has come into the city today, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7404P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7404P\"></sup>the people have a sacrifice on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7404Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7404Q\"></sup>the high place today.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>As soon as you enter the city you will find him before he goes up to the high place to eat, for the people will not eat until he comes, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7405R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7405R\"></sup>he must bless the sacrifice; afterward those who are invited will eat. Now therefore, go up for you will find him at once.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So they went up to the city. As they came into the city, behold, Samuel was coming out toward them to go up to the high place.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now a day before Saul’s coming, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7407S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7407S\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had revealed <i>this</i> to Samuel saying,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“About this time tomorrow I will send you a man from the land of Benjamin, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7408T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7408T\"></sup>you shall anoint him to be prince over My people Israel; and he will deliver My people from the hand of the Philistines. For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7408U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7408U\"></sup>I have regarded My people, because their cry has come to Me.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When Samuel saw Saul, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7409V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7409V\"></sup>Behold, the man of whom I spoke to you! This one shall rule over My people.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Saul approached Samuel in the gate and said, “Please tell me where the seer’s house is.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Samuel answered Saul and said, “I am the seer. Go up before me to the high place, for you shall eat with me today; and in the morning I will let you go, and will tell you all that is on your mind.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7412W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7412W\"></sup>As for your donkeys which were lost three days ago, do not set your mind on them, for they have been found. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7412X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7412X\"></sup>for whom is all that is desirable in Israel? Is it not for you and for all your father’s household?”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Saul replied, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7413Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7413Y\"></sup>Am I not a Benjamite, of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7413Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7413Z\"></sup>the smallest of the tribes of Israel, and my family the least of all the families of the tribe of Benjamin? Why then do you speak to me in this way?”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Samuel took Saul and his servant and brought them into the hall and gave them a place at the head of those who were invited, who were about thirty men.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Samuel said to the cook, “Bring the portion that I gave you, concerning which I said to you, ‘Set it aside.’”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then the cook <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7416AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7416AA\"></sup>took up the leg with what was on it and set <i>it</i> before Saul. And <i>Samuel</i> said, “Here is what has been reserved! Set <i>it</i> before you <i>and</i> eat, because it has been kept for you until the appointed time, since I said I have invited the people.” So Saul ate with Samuel that day.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>When they came down from the high place into the city, <i>Samuel</i> spoke with Saul <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7417AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7417AB\"></sup>on the roof.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And they arose early; and at daybreak Samuel called to Saul on the roof, saying, “Get up, that I may send you away.” So Saul arose, and both he and Samuel went out into the street.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>As they were going down to the edge of the city, Samuel said to Saul, “Say to the servant that he might go ahead of us and pass on, but you remain standing now, that I may proclaim the word of God to you.”"
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7420A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7420A\"></sup>Samuel took the flask of oil, poured it on his head, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7420B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7420B\"></sup>kissed him and said, “Has not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7420C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7420C\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> anointed you a ruler over <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7420D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7420D\"></sup>His inheritance?",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>When you go from me today, then you will find two men close to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7421E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7421E\"></sup>Rachel’s tomb in the territory of Benjamin at Zelzah; and they will say to you, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7421F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7421F\"></sup>The donkeys which you went to look for have been found. Now behold, your father has ceased to be concerned about the donkeys and is anxious for you, saying, “What shall I do about my son?”’",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then you will go on further from there, and you will come as far as the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7422G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7422G\"></sup>oak of Tabor, and there three men going up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7422H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7422H\"></sup>to God at Bethel will meet you, one carrying three young goats, another carrying three loaves of bread, and another carrying a jug of wine;",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and they will greet you and give you two <i>loaves</i> of bread, which you will accept from their hand.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Afterward you will come to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7424I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7424I\"></sup>the hill of God where the Philistine garrison is; and it shall be as soon as you have come there to the city, that you will meet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7424J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7424J\"></sup>a group of prophets coming down from the high place with harp, tambourine, flute, and a lyre before them, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7424K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7424K\"></sup>they will be prophesying.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7425L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7425L\"></sup>the Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will come upon you mightily, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7425M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7425M\"></sup>you shall prophesy with them and be changed into another man.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>It shall be when these signs come to you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7426N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7426N\"></sup>do for yourself what the occasion requires, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7426O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7426O\"></sup>God is with you.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7427P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7427P\"></sup>you shall go down before me to Gilgal; and behold, I will come down to you to offer burnt offerings and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7427Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7427Q\"></sup>sacrifice peace offerings. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7427R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7427R\"></sup>You shall wait seven days until I come to you and show you what you should do.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then it happened when he turned his back to leave Samuel, God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7428S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7428S\"></sup>changed his heart; and all those signs came about on that day.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7429T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7429T\"></sup>When they came to the hill there, behold, a group of prophets met him; and the Spirit of God came upon him mightily, so that he prophesied among them.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>It came about, when all who knew him previously saw that he prophesied now with the prophets, that the people said to one another, “What has happened to the son of Kish? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7430U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7430U\"></sup>Is Saul also among the prophets?”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>A man there said, “Now, who is their father?” Therefore it became a proverb: “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7431V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7431V\"></sup>Is Saul also among the prophets?”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When he had finished prophesying, he came to the high place.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7433W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7433W\"></sup>Saul’s uncle said to him and his servant, “Where did you go?” And he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7433X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7433X\"></sup>To look for the donkeys. When we saw that they could not be found, we went to Samuel.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Saul’s uncle said, “Please tell me what Samuel said to you.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So Saul said to his uncle, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7435Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7435Y\"></sup>He told us plainly that the donkeys had been found.” But he did not tell him about the matter of the kingdom which Samuel had mentioned.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Thereafter Samuel called the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7436Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7436Z\"></sup>people together to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at Mizpah;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and he said to the sons of Israel, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7437AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7437AA\"></sup>Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, ‘I brought Israel up from Egypt, and I delivered you from the hand of the Egyptians and from the power of all the kingdoms that were oppressing you.’",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7438AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7438AB\"></sup>have today rejected your God, who delivers you from all your calamities and your distresses; yet you have said, ‘No, but set a king over us!’ Now therefore, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7438AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7438AC\"></sup>present yourselves before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by your tribes and by your clans.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Thus Samuel brought all the tribes of Israel near, and the tribe of Benjamin was taken by lot.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then he brought the tribe of Benjamin near by its families, and the Matrite family was taken. And Saul the son of Kish was taken; but when they looked for him, he could not be found.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Therefore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7441AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7441AD\"></sup>they inquired further of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “Has the man come here yet?” So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “Behold, he is hiding himself by the baggage.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So they ran and took him from there, and when he stood among the people, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7442AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7442AE\"></sup>he was taller than any of the people from his shoulders upward.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Samuel said to all the people, “Do you see him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7443AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7443AF\"></sup>whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has chosen? Surely there is no one like him among all the people.” So all the people shouted and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7443AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7443AG\"></sup><i>Long</i> live the king!”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then Samuel told the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7444AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7444AH\"></sup>the ordinances of the kingdom, and wrote <i>them</i> in the book and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7444AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7444AI\"></sup>placed <i>it</i> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. And Samuel sent all the people away, each one to his house.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Saul also went <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7445AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7445AJ\"></sup>to his house at Gibeah; and the valiant <i>men</i> whose hearts God had touched went with him.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But certain <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7446AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7446AK\"></sup>worthless men said, “How can this one deliver us?” And they despised him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7446AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7446AL\"></sup>did not bring him any present. But he kept silent."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7447A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7447A\"></sup>Nahash the Ammonite came up and besieged <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7447B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7447B\"></sup>Jabesh-gilead; and all the men of Jabesh said to Nahash, “Make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7447C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7447C\"></sup>a covenant with us and we will serve you.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But Nahash the Ammonite said to them, “I will make <i>it</i> with you on this condition, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7448D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7448D\"></sup>that I will gouge out the right eye of every one of you, thus I will make it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7448E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7448E\"></sup>a reproach on all Israel.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7449F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7449F\"></sup>The elders of Jabesh said to him, “Let us alone for seven days, that we may send messengers throughout the territory of Israel. Then, if there is no one to deliver us, we will come out to you.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the messengers came <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7450G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7450G\"></sup>to Gibeah of Saul and spoke these words in the hearing of the people, and all the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7450H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7450H\"></sup>lifted up their voices and wept.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now behold, Saul was coming from the field <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7451I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7451I\"></sup>behind the oxen, and he said, “What is <i>the matter</i> with the people that they weep?” So they related to him the words of the men of Jabesh.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7452J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7452J\"></sup>the Spirit of God came upon Saul mightily when he heard these words, and he became very angry.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He took a yoke of oxen and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7453K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7453K\"></sup>cut them in pieces, and sent <i>them</i> throughout the territory of Israel by the hand of messengers, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7453L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7453L\"></sup>Whoever does not come out after Saul and after Samuel, so shall it be done to his oxen.” Then the dread of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> fell on the people, and they came out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7453M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7453M\"></sup>as one man.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He numbered them in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7454N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7454N\"></sup>Bezek; and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7454O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7454O\"></sup>sons of Israel were 300,000, and the men of Judah 30,000.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>They said to the messengers who had come, “Thus you shall say to the men of Jabesh-gilead, ‘Tomorrow, by the time the sun is hot, you will have deliverance.’” So the messengers went and told the men of Jabesh; and they were glad.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then the men of Jabesh said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7456P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7456P\"></sup>Tomorrow we will come out to you, and you may do to us whatever seems good to you.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The next morning Saul put the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7457Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7457Q\"></sup>in three companies; and they came into the midst of the camp at the morning watch and struck down the Ammonites until the heat of the day. Those who survived were scattered, so that no two of them were left together.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then the people said to Samuel, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7458R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7458R\"></sup>Who is he that said, ‘Shall Saul reign over us?’ <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7458S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7458S\"></sup>Bring the men, that we may put them to death.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But Saul said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7459T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7459T\"></sup>Not a man shall be put to death this day, for today <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7459U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7459U\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has accomplished deliverance in Israel.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then Samuel said to the people, “Come and let us go to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7460V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7460V\"></sup>Gilgal and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7460W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7460W\"></sup>renew the kingdom there.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So all the people went to Gilgal, and there they made Saul king <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7461X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7461X\"></sup>before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in Gilgal. There they also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7461Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7461Y\"></sup>offered sacrifices of peace offerings before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; and there Saul and all the men of Israel rejoiced greatly."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>Then Samuel said to all Israel, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7462A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7462A\"></sup>I have listened to your voice in all that you said to me and I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7462B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7462B\"></sup>have appointed a king over you.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Now, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7463C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7463C\"></sup>here is the king walking before you, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7463D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7463D\"></sup>I am old and gray, and behold <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7463E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7463E\"></sup>my sons are with you. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7463F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7463F\"></sup>I have walked before you from my youth even to this day.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Here I am; bear witness against me before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7464G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7464G\"></sup>His anointed. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7464H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7464H\"></sup>Whose ox have I taken, or whose donkey have I taken, or whom have I defrauded? Whom have I oppressed, or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7464I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7464I\"></sup>from whose hand have I taken a bribe to blind my eyes with it? I will restore <i>it</i> to you.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They said, “You have not defrauded us or oppressed us or taken anything from any man’s hand.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He said to them, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is witness against you, and His anointed is witness this day that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7466J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7466J\"></sup>you have found nothing <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7466K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7466K\"></sup>in my hand.” And they said, “<i>He is</i> witness.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Samuel said to the people, “It is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7467L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7467L\"></sup>appointed Moses and Aaron and who brought your fathers up from the land of Egypt.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So now, take your stand, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7468M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7468M\"></sup>that I may plead with you before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> concerning all the righteous acts of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> which He did for you and your fathers.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7469N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7469N\"></sup>When Jacob went into Egypt and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7469O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7469O\"></sup>your fathers cried out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7469P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7469P\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent Moses and Aaron <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7469Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7469Q\"></sup>who brought your fathers out of Egypt and settled them in this place.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7470R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7470R\"></sup>they forgot the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God, so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7470S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7470S\"></sup>He sold them into the hand of Sisera, captain of the army of Hazor, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7470T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7470T\"></sup>into the hand of the Philistines and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7470U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7470U\"></sup>into the hand of the king of Moab, and they fought against them.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7471V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7471V\"></sup>They cried out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and said, ‘We have sinned because we have forsaken the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and have served <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7471W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7471W\"></sup>the Baals and the Ashtaroth; but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7471X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7471X\"></sup>now deliver us from the hands of our enemies, and we will serve You.’",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7472Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7472Y\"></sup>Jerubbaal and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7472Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7472Z\"></sup>Bedan and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7472AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7472AA\"></sup>Jephthah and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7472AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7472AB\"></sup>Samuel, and delivered you from the hands of your enemies all around, so that you lived in security.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When you saw <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7473AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7473AC\"></sup>that Nahash the king of the sons of Ammon came against you, you said to me, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7473AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7473AD\"></sup>No, but a king shall reign over us,’ <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7473AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7473AE\"></sup>although the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God <i>was</i> your king.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now therefore, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7474AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7474AF\"></sup>here is the king whom you have chosen, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7474AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7474AG\"></sup>whom you have asked for, and behold, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has set a king over you.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7475AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7475AH\"></sup>If you will fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and serve Him, and listen to His voice and not rebel against the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, then both you and also the king who reigns over you will follow the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7476AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7476AI\"></sup>If you will not listen to the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but rebel against the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7476AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7476AJ\"></sup>the hand of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will be against you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7476AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7476AK\"></sup><i>as it was</i> against your fathers.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Even now, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7477AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7477AL\"></sup>take your stand and see this great thing which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will do before your eyes.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7478AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7478AM\"></sup>Is it not the wheat harvest today? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7478AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7478AN\"></sup>I will call to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, that He may send thunder and rain. Then you will know and see that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7478AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7478AO\"></sup>your wickedness is great which you have done in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by asking for yourselves a king.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So Samuel called to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent thunder and rain that day; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7479AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7479AP\"></sup>all the people greatly feared the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and Samuel.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then all the people said to Samuel, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7480AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7480AQ\"></sup>Pray for your servants to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, so that we may not die, for we have added to all our sins <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7480AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7480AR\"></sup><i>this</i> evil by asking for ourselves a king.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Samuel said to the people, “Do not fear. You have committed all this evil, yet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7481AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7481AS\"></sup>do not turn aside from following the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with all your heart.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>You must not turn aside, for <i>then you would go</i> after <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7482AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7482AT\"></sup>futile things which can not profit or deliver, because they are futile.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7483AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7483AU\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will not abandon His people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7483AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7483AV\"></sup>on account of His great name, because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7483AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7483AW\"></sup>has been pleased to make you a people for Himself.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Moreover, as for me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7484AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7484AX\"></sup>far be it from me that I should sin against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by ceasing to pray for you; but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7484AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7484AY\"></sup>I will instruct you in the good and right way.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7485AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7485AZ\"></sup>Only fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and serve Him in truth with all your heart; for consider <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7485BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7485BA\"></sup>what great things He has done for you.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7486BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7486BB\"></sup>But if you still do wickedly, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7486BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7486BC\"></sup>both you and your king <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7486BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7486BD\"></sup>will be swept away.”"
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>Saul was <i>thirty</i> years old when he began to reign, and he reigned <i>forty</i> two years over Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Now Saul chose for himself 3,000 men of Israel, of which 2,000 were with Saul in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7488A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7488A\"></sup>Michmash and in the hill country of Bethel, while 1,000 were with Jonathan at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7488B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7488B\"></sup>Gibeah of Benjamin. But he sent away the rest of the people, each to his tent.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Jonathan smote <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7489C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7489C\"></sup>the garrison of the Philistines that was in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7489D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7489D\"></sup>Geba, and the Philistines heard of <i>it</i>. Then Saul <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7489E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7489E\"></sup>blew the trumpet throughout the land, saying, “Let the Hebrews hear.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>All Israel heard the news that Saul had smitten the garrison of the Philistines, and also that Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7490F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7490F\"></sup>had become odious to the Philistines. The people were then summoned to Saul at Gilgal.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now the Philistines assembled to fight with Israel, 30,000 chariots and 6,000 horsemen, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7491G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7491G\"></sup>people like the sand which is on the seashore in abundance; and they came up and camped in Michmash, east of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7491H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7491H\"></sup>Beth-aven.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When the men of Israel saw that they were in a strait (for the people were hard-pressed), then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7492I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7492I\"></sup>the people hid themselves in caves, in thickets, in cliffs, in cellars, and in pits.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Also <i>some of</i> the Hebrews crossed the Jordan into the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7493J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7493J\"></sup>Gad and Gilead. But as for Saul, he <i>was</i> still in Gilgal, and all the people followed him trembling.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7494K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7494K\"></sup>he waited seven days, according to the appointed time set by Samuel, but Samuel did not come to Gilgal; and the people were scattering from him.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So Saul said, “Bring to me the burnt offering and the peace offerings.” And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7495L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7495L\"></sup>he offered the burnt offering.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>As soon as he finished offering the burnt offering, behold, Samuel came; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7496M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7496M\"></sup>Saul went out to meet him <i>and</i> to greet him.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But Samuel said, “What have you done?” And Saul said, “Because I saw that the people were scattering from me, and that you did not come within the appointed days, and that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7497N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7497N\"></sup>the Philistines were assembling at Michmash,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>therefore I said, ‘Now the Philistines will come down against me at Gilgal, and I have not asked the favor of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.’ So I forced myself and offered the burnt offering.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Samuel said to Saul, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7499O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7499O\"></sup>You have acted foolishly; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7499P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7499P\"></sup>you have not kept the commandment of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, which He commanded you, for now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> would have established your kingdom over Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7499Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7499Q\"></sup>forever.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7500R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7500R\"></sup>now your kingdom shall not endure. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7500S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7500S\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has sought out for Himself a man after His own heart, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has appointed him as ruler over His people, because you have not kept what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded you.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then Samuel arose and went up from Gilgal to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7501T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7501T\"></sup>Gibeah of Benjamin. And Saul numbered the people who were present with him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7501U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7501U\"></sup>about six hundred men.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Now Saul and his son Jonathan and the people who were present with them were staying in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7502V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7502V\"></sup>Geba of Benjamin while the Philistines camped at Michmash.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7503W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7503W\"></sup>the raiders came from the camp of the Philistines in three companies: one company turned toward <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7503X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7503X\"></sup>Ophrah, to the land of Shual,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and another company turned toward <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7504Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7504Y\"></sup>Beth-horon, and another company turned toward the border which overlooks the valley of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7504Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7504Z\"></sup>Zeboim toward the wilderness.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7505AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7505AA\"></sup>no blacksmith could be found in all the land of Israel, for the Philistines said, “Otherwise the Hebrews will make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7505AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7505AB\"></sup>swords or spears.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So all Israel went down to the Philistines, each to sharpen his plowshare, his mattock, his axe, and his hoe.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The charge was two-thirds of a shekel for the plowshares, the mattocks, the forks, and the axes, and to fix the hoes.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So it came about on the day of battle that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7508AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7508AC\"></sup>neither sword nor spear was found in the hands of any of the people who <i>were</i> with Saul and Jonathan, but they were found with Saul and his son Jonathan.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7509AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7509AD\"></sup>the garrison of the Philistines went out to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7509AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7509AE\"></sup>the pass of Michmash."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span>Now the day came that Jonathan, the son of Saul, said to the young man who was carrying his armor, “Come and let us cross over to the Philistines’ garrison that is on the other side.” But he did not tell his father.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Saul was staying in the outskirts of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7511A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7511A\"></sup>Gibeah under the pomegranate tree which is in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7511B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7511B\"></sup>Migron. And the people who <i>were</i> with him <i>were</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7511C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7511C\"></sup>about six hundred men,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and Ahijah, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7512D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7512D\"></sup>son of Ahitub, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7512E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7512E\"></sup>Ichabod’s brother, the son of Phinehas, the son of Eli, the priest of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7512F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7512F\"></sup>Shiloh, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7512G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7512G\"></sup>was wearing an ephod. And the people did not know that Jonathan had gone.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7513H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7513H\"></sup>Between the passes by which Jonathan sought to cross over to the Philistines’ garrison, there was a sharp crag on the one side and a sharp crag on the other side, and the name of the one was Bozez, and the name of the other Seneh.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The one crag rose on the north opposite Michmash, and the other on the south opposite Geba.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Jonathan said to the young man who was carrying his armor, “Come and let us cross over to the garrison of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7515I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7515I\"></sup>these uncircumcised; perhaps the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will work for us, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7515J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7515J\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is not restrained to save by many or by few.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>His armor bearer said to him, “Do all that is in your heart; turn yourself, <i>and</i> here I am with you according to your desire.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Jonathan said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7517K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7517K\"></sup>Behold, we will cross over to the men and reveal ourselves to them.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>If they say to us, ‘Wait until we come to you’; then we will stand in our place and not go up to them.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But if they say, ‘Come up to us,’ then we will go up, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given them into our hands; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7519L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7519L\"></sup>this shall be the sign to us.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When both of them revealed themselves to the garrison of the Philistines, the Philistines said, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7520M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7520M\"></sup>Hebrews are coming out of the holes where they have hidden themselves.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So the men of the garrison hailed Jonathan and his armor bearer and said, “Come up to us and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7521N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7521N\"></sup>we will tell you something.” And Jonathan said to his armor bearer, “Come up after me, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7521O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7521O\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given them into the hands of Israel.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then Jonathan climbed up on his hands and feet, with his armor bearer behind him; and they fell before Jonathan, and his armor bearer put some to death after him.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>That first slaughter which Jonathan and his armor bearer made was about twenty men within about half a furrow in an acre of land.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And there was a trembling in the camp, in the field, and among all the people. Even the garrison and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7524P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7524P\"></sup>the raiders trembled, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7524Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7524Q\"></sup>the earth quaked so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7524R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7524R\"></sup>that it became a great trembling.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Now Saul’s watchmen in Gibeah of Benjamin looked, and behold, the multitude melted away; and they went here and <i>there</i>.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Saul said to the people who <i>were</i> with him, “Number now and see who has gone from us.” And when they had numbered, behold, Jonathan and his armor bearer were not <i>there</i>.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Saul said to Ahijah, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7527S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7527S\"></sup>Bring the ark of God here.” For the ark of God was at that time with the sons of Israel.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7528T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7528T\"></sup>While Saul talked to the priest, the commotion in the camp of the Philistines continued and increased; so Saul said to the priest, “Withdraw your hand.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Saul and all the people who <i>were</i> with him rallied and came to the battle; and behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7529U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7529U\"></sup>every man’s sword was against his fellow, <i>and there was</i> very great confusion.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Now the Hebrews <i>who</i> were with the Philistines previously, who went up with them all around in the camp, even <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7530V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7530V\"></sup>they also <i>turned</i> to be with the Israelites who <i>were</i> with Saul and Jonathan.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When all the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7531W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7531W\"></sup>men of Israel who had hidden themselves in the hill country of Ephraim heard that the Philistines had fled, even they also pursued them closely in the battle.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7532X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7532X\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> delivered Israel that day, and the battle spread beyond <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7532Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7532Y\"></sup>Beth-aven.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Now the men of Israel were hard-pressed on that day, for Saul had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7533Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7533Z\"></sup>put the people under oath, saying, “Cursed be the man who eats food before evening, and until I have avenged myself on my enemies.” So none of the people tasted food.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>All <i>the people of</i> the land entered the forest, and there was honey on the ground.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>When the people entered the forest, behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7535AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7535AA\"></sup><i>there was</i> a flow of honey; but no man put his hand to his mouth, for the people feared the oath.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But Jonathan had not heard when his father put the people under oath; therefore, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7536AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7536AB\"></sup>he put out the end of the staff that <i>was</i> in his hand and dipped it in the honeycomb, and put his hand to his mouth, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7536AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7536AC\"></sup>his eyes brightened.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then one of the people said, “Your father strictly put the people under oath, saying, ‘Cursed be the man who eats food today.’” And the people were weary.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then Jonathan said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7538AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7538AD\"></sup>My father has troubled the land. See now, how my eyes have brightened because I tasted a little of this honey.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>How much more, if only the people had eaten freely today of the spoil of their enemies which they found! For now the slaughter among the Philistines has not been great.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>They struck among the Philistines that day from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7540AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7540AE\"></sup>Michmash to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7540AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7540AF\"></sup>Aijalon. And the people were very weary.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7541AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7541AG\"></sup>The people rushed greedily upon the spoil, and took sheep and oxen and calves, and slew <i>them</i> on the ground; and the people ate <i>them</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7541AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7541AH\"></sup>with the blood.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Then they told Saul, saying, “Behold, the people are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7542AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7542AI\"></sup>sinning against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by eating with the blood.” And he said, “You have acted treacherously; roll a great stone to me today.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Saul said, “Disperse yourselves among the people and say to them, ‘Each one of you bring me his ox or his sheep, and slaughter <i>it</i> here and eat; and do not sin against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by eating with the blood.’” So all the people that night brought each one his ox with him and slaughtered <i>it</i> there.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7544AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7544AJ\"></sup>Saul built an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; it was the first altar that he built to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Then Saul said, “Let us go down after the Philistines by night and take spoil among them until the morning light, and let us not leave a man of them.” And they said, “Do whatever seems good to you.” So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7545AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7545AK\"></sup>the priest said, “Let us draw near to God here.”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Saul <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7546AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7546AL\"></sup>inquired of God, “Shall I go down after the Philistines? Will You give them into the hand of Israel?” But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7546AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7546AM\"></sup>He did not answer him on that day.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Saul said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7547AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7547AN\"></sup>Draw near here, all you chiefs of the people, and investigate and see how this sin has happened today.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7548AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7548AO\"></sup>as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, who delivers Israel, though it is in Jonathan my son, he shall surely die.” But not one of all the people answered him.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Then he said to all Israel, “You shall be on one side and I and Jonathan my son will be on the other side.” And the people said to Saul, “Do what seems good to you.”",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Therefore, Saul said to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7550AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7550AP\"></sup>Give a perfect <i>lot</i>.” And Jonathan and Saul were taken, but the people escaped.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Saul said, “Cast <i>lots</i> between me and Jonathan my son.” And Jonathan was taken.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Then Saul said to Jonathan, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7552AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7552AQ\"></sup>Tell me what you have done.” So Jonathan told him and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7552AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7552AR\"></sup>I indeed tasted a little honey with the end of the staff that was in my hand. Here I am, I must die!”",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Saul said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7553AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7553AS\"></sup>May God do this <i>to me</i> and more also, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7553AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7553AT\"></sup>you shall surely die, Jonathan.”",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>But the people said to Saul, “Must Jonathan die, who has brought about this great deliverance in Israel? Far from it! As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7554AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7554AU\"></sup>not one hair of his head shall fall to the ground, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7554AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7554AV\"></sup>he has worked with God this day.” So the people rescued Jonathan and he did not die.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Then Saul went up from pursuing the Philistines, and the Philistines went to their own place.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>Now when Saul had taken the kingdom over Israel, he fought against all his enemies on every side, against Moab, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7556AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7556AW\"></sup>the sons of Ammon, Edom, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7556AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7556AX\"></sup>the kings of Zobah, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7556AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7556AY\"></sup>the Philistines; and wherever he turned, he inflicted punishment.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>He acted valiantly and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7557AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7557AZ\"></sup>defeated the Amalekites, and delivered Israel from the hands of those who plundered them.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7558BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7558BA\"></sup>the sons of Saul were Jonathan and Ishvi and Malchi-shua; and the names of his two daughters <i>were these</i>: the name of the firstborn <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7558BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7558BB\"></sup>Merab and the name of the younger <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7558BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7558BC\"></sup>Michal.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>The name of Saul’s wife was Ahinoam the daughter of Ahimaaz. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7559BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7559BD\"></sup>the name of the captain of his army was Abner the son of Ner, Saul’s uncle.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7560BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7560BE\"></sup>Kish <i>was</i> the father of Saul, and Ner the father of Abner <i>was</i> the son of Abiel.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>Now the war against the Philistines was severe all the days of Saul; and when Saul saw any mighty man or any valiant man, he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7561BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7561BF\"></sup>attached him to his staff."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>Then Samuel said to Saul, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7562A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7562A\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent me to anoint you as king over His people, over Israel; now therefore, listen to the words of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of hosts, ‘I will punish Amalek <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7563B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7563B\"></sup><i>for</i> what he did to Israel, how he set himself against him on the way while he was coming up from Egypt.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now go and strike Amalek and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7564C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7564C\"></sup>utterly destroy all that he has, and do not spare him; but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7564D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7564D\"></sup>put to death both man and woman, child and infant, ox and sheep, camel and donkey.’”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then Saul summoned the people and numbered them in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7565E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7565E\"></sup>Telaim, 200,000 foot soldiers and 10,000 men of Judah.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Saul came to the city of Amalek and set an ambush in the valley.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Saul said to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7567F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7567F\"></sup>the Kenites, “Go, depart, go down from among the Amalekites, so that I do not destroy you with them; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7567G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7567G\"></sup>you showed kindness to all the sons of Israel when they came up from Egypt.” So the Kenites departed from among the Amalekites.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7568H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7568H\"></sup>Saul defeated the Amalekites, from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7568I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7568I\"></sup>Havilah as you go to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7568J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7568J\"></sup>Shur, which is east of Egypt.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He captured <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7569K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7569K\"></sup>Agag the king of the Amalekites alive, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7569L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7569L\"></sup>utterly destroyed all the people with the edge of the sword.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But Saul and the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7570M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7570M\"></sup>spared Agag and the best of the sheep, the oxen, the fatlings, the lambs, and all that was good, and were not willing to destroy them utterly; but everything despised and worthless, that they utterly destroyed.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to Samuel, saying,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7572N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7572N\"></sup>I regret that I have made Saul king, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7572O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7572O\"></sup>he has turned back from following Me and has not carried out My commands.” And Samuel was distressed and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7572P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7572P\"></sup>cried out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> all night.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Samuel rose early in the morning to meet Saul; and it was told Samuel, saying, “Saul came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7573Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7573Q\"></sup>Carmel, and behold, he set up a monument for himself, then turned and proceeded on down to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7573R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7573R\"></sup>Gilgal.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Samuel came to Saul, and Saul said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7574S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7574S\"></sup>Blessed are you of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>! I have carried out the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But Samuel said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7575T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7575T\"></sup>What then is this bleating of the sheep in my ears, and the lowing of the oxen which I hear?”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Saul said, “They have brought them from the Amalekites, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7576U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7576U\"></sup>the people spared the best of the sheep and oxen, to sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God; but the rest we have utterly destroyed.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Samuel said to Saul, “Wait, and let me tell you what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me last night.” And he said to him, “Speak!”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Samuel said, “Is it not true, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7578V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7578V\"></sup>though you were little in your own eyes, you were <i>made</i> the head of the tribes of Israel? And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> anointed you king over Israel,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent you on a mission, and said, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7579W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7579W\"></sup>Go and utterly destroy the sinners, the Amalekites, and fight against them until they are exterminated.’",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Why then did you not obey the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7580X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7580X\"></sup>but rushed upon the spoil and did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Saul said to Samuel, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7581Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7581Y\"></sup>I did obey the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and went on the mission on which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent me, and have brought back Agag the king of Amalek, and have utterly destroyed the Amalekites.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7582Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7582Z\"></sup>the people took <i>some</i> of the spoil, sheep and oxen, the choicest of the things devoted to destruction, to sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God at Gilgal.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Samuel said,“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7583AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7583AA\"></sup>Has the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as much delight in burnt offerings and sacrificesAs in obeying the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7583AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7583AB\"></sup>to obey is better than sacrifice,<i>And</i> to heed than the fat of rams.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“For rebellion is as the sin of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7584AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7584AC\"></sup>divination,And insubordination is as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7584AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7584AD\"></sup>iniquity and idolatry.Because you have rejected the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7584AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7584AE\"></sup>He has also rejected you from <i>being</i> king.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then Saul said to Samuel, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7585AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7585AF\"></sup>I have sinned; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7585AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7585AG\"></sup>I have indeed transgressed the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and your words, because I feared the people and listened to their voice.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Now therefore, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7586AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7586AH\"></sup>please pardon my sin and return with me, that I may worship the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But Samuel said to Saul, “I will not return with you; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7587AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7587AI\"></sup>you have rejected the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has rejected you from being king over Israel.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>As Samuel turned to go, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7588AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7588AJ\"></sup><i>Saul</i> seized the edge of his robe, and it tore.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So Samuel said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7589AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7589AK\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has torn the kingdom of Israel from you today and has given it to your neighbor, who is better than you.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Also the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7590AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7590AL\"></sup>Glory of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7590AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7590AM\"></sup>will not lie or change His mind; for He is not a man that He should change His mind.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then he said, “I have sinned; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7591AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7591AN\"></sup><i>but</i> please honor me now before the elders of my people and before Israel, and go back with me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7591AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7591AO\"></sup>that I may worship the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>So Samuel went back following Saul, and Saul worshiped the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Then Samuel said, “Bring me Agag, the king of the Amalekites.” And Agag came to him cheerfully. And Agag said, “Surely the bitterness of death is past.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>But Samuel said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7594AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7594AP\"></sup>As your sword has made women childless, so shall your mother be childless among women.” And Samuel hewed Agag to pieces before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at Gilgal.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then Samuel went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7595AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7595AQ\"></sup>Ramah, but Saul went up to his house at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7595AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7595AR\"></sup>Gibeah of Saul.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7596AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7596AS\"></sup>Samuel did not see Saul again until the day of his death; for Samuel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7596AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7596AT\"></sup>grieved over Saul. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> regretted that He had made Saul king over Israel."
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Samuel, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7597A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7597A\"></sup>How long will you grieve over Saul, since <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7597B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7597B\"></sup>I have rejected him from being king over Israel? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7597C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7597C\"></sup>Fill your horn with oil and go; I will send you to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7597D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7597D\"></sup>Jesse the Bethlehemite, for I have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7597E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7597E\"></sup>selected a king for Myself among his sons.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But Samuel said, “How can I go? When Saul hears <i>of it</i>, he will kill me.” And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7598F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7598F\"></sup>Take a heifer with you and say, ‘I have come to sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.’",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You shall invite Jesse to the sacrifice, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7599G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7599G\"></sup>I will show you what you shall do; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7599H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7599H\"></sup>you shall anoint for Me the one whom I designate to you.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Samuel did what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, and came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7600I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7600I\"></sup>Bethlehem. And the elders of the city came trembling to meet him and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7600J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7600J\"></sup>Do you come in peace?”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He said, “In peace; I have come to sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7601K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7601K\"></sup>Consecrate yourselves and come with me to the sacrifice.” He also consecrated Jesse and his sons and invited them to the sacrifice.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When they entered, he looked at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7602L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7602L\"></sup>Eliab and thought, “Surely the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> anointed is before Him.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Samuel, “Do not look at his appearance or at the height of his stature, because I have rejected him; for God <i>sees</i> not as man sees, for man looks at the outward appearance, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7603M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7603M\"></sup>but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> looks at the heart.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Jesse called <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7604N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7604N\"></sup>Abinadab and made him pass before Samuel. And he said, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has not chosen this one either.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Next Jesse made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7605O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7605O\"></sup>Shammah pass by. And he said, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has not chosen this one either.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Thus Jesse made seven of his sons pass before Samuel. But Samuel said to Jesse, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has not chosen these.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And Samuel said to Jesse, “Are these all the children?” And he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7607P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7607P\"></sup>There remains yet the youngest, and behold, he is tending the sheep.” Then Samuel said to Jesse, “Send and bring him; for we will not sit down until he comes here.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So he sent and brought him in. Now he was ruddy, with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7608Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7608Q\"></sup>beautiful eyes and a handsome appearance. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7608R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7608R\"></sup>Arise, anoint him; for this is he.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then Samuel took the horn of oil and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7609S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7609S\"></sup>anointed him in the midst of his brothers; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7609T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7609T\"></sup>the Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came mightily upon David from that day forward. And Samuel arose and went to Ramah.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7610U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7610U\"></sup>Now the Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> departed from Saul, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7610V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7610V\"></sup>an evil spirit from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> terrorized him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Saul’s servants then said to him, “Behold now, an evil spirit from God is terrorizing you.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Let our lord now command your servants who are before you. Let them seek a man who is a skillful player on the harp; and it shall come about when the evil spirit from God is on you, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7612W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7612W\"></sup>he shall play <i>the harp</i> with his hand, and you will be well.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So Saul said to his servants, “Provide for me now a man who can play well and bring <i>him</i> to me.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then one of the young men said, “Behold, I have seen a son of Jesse the Bethlehemite who is a skillful musician, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7614X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7614X\"></sup>a mighty man of valor, a warrior, one prudent in speech, and a handsome man; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7614Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7614Y\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is with him.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So Saul sent messengers to Jesse and said, “Send me your son David who is with the flock.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Jesse <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7616Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7616Z\"></sup>took a donkey <i>loaded with</i> bread and a jug of wine and a young goat, and sent <i>them</i> to Saul by David his son.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then David came to Saul and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7617AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7617AA\"></sup>attended him; and Saul loved him greatly, and he became his armor bearer.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Saul sent to Jesse, saying, “Let David now stand before me, for he has found favor in my sight.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So it came about whenever <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7619AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7619AB\"></sup>the <i>evil</i> spirit from God came to Saul, David would take the harp and play <i>it</i> with his hand; and Saul would be refreshed and be well, and the evil spirit would depart from him."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7620A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7620A\"></sup>the Philistines gathered their armies for battle; and they were gathered at Socoh which belongs to Judah, and they camped between <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7620B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7620B\"></sup>Socoh and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7620C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7620C\"></sup>Azekah, in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7620D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7620D\"></sup>Ephes-dammim.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Saul and the men of Israel were gathered and camped in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7621E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7621E\"></sup>the valley of Elah, and drew up in battle array to encounter the Philistines.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The Philistines stood on the mountain on one side while Israel stood on the mountain on the other side, with the valley between them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then a champion came out from the armies of the Philistines named <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7623F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7623F\"></sup>Goliath, from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7623G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7623G\"></sup>Gath, whose height was six cubits and a span.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><i>He had</i> a bronze helmet on his head, and he was clothed with scale-armor which weighed five thousand shekels of bronze.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><i>He</i> also <i>had</i> bronze greaves on his legs and a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7625H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7625H\"></sup>bronze javelin <i>slung</i> between his shoulders.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7626I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7626I\"></sup>The shaft of his spear was like a weaver’s beam, and the head of his spear <i>weighed</i> six hundred shekels of iron; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7626J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7626J\"></sup>his shield-carrier also walked before him.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He stood and shouted to the ranks of Israel and said to them, “Why do you come out to draw up in battle array? Am I not the Philistine and you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7627K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7627K\"></sup>servants of Saul? Choose a man for yourselves and let him come down to me.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7628L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7628L\"></sup>If he is able to fight with me and kill me, then we will become your servants; but if I prevail against him and kill him, then you shall become our servants and serve us.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Again the Philistine said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7629M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7629M\"></sup>I defy the ranks of Israel this day; give me a man that we may fight together.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When Saul and all Israel heard these words of the Philistine, they were dismayed and greatly afraid.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now David was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7631N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7631N\"></sup>the son of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7631O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7631O\"></sup>Ephrathite of Bethlehem in Judah, whose name was Jesse, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7631P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7631P\"></sup>he had eight sons. And Jesse was old in the days of Saul, advanced <i>in years</i> among men.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The three older sons of Jesse had gone after Saul to the battle. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7632Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7632Q\"></sup>the names of his three sons who went to the battle were Eliab the firstborn, and the second to him Abinadab, and the third Shammah.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7633R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7633R\"></sup>David was the youngest. Now the three oldest followed Saul,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7634S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7634S\"></sup>but David went back and forth from Saul <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7634T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7634T\"></sup>to tend his father’s flock at Bethlehem.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The Philistine came forward morning and evening for forty days and took his stand.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Jesse said to David his son, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7636U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7636U\"></sup>Take now for your brothers an ephah of this roasted grain and these ten loaves and run to the camp to your brothers.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7637V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7637V\"></sup>Bring also these ten cuts of cheese to the commander of <i>their</i> thousand, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7637W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7637W\"></sup>and look into the welfare of your brothers, and bring back news of them.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>For Saul and they and all the men of Israel are in the valley of Elah, fighting with the Philistines.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So David arose early in the morning and left the flock with a keeper and took <i>the supplies</i> and went as Jesse had commanded him. And he came to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7639X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7639X\"></sup>circle of the camp while the army was going out in battle array shouting the war cry.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Israel and the Philistines drew up in battle array, army against army.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then David left his <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7641Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7641Y\"></sup>baggage in the care of the baggage keeper, and ran to the battle line and entered in order to greet his brothers.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>As he was talking with them, behold, the champion, the Philistine from Gath named Goliath, was coming up from the army of the Philistines, and he spoke <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7642Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7642Z\"></sup>these same words; and David heard <i>them</i>.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When all the men of Israel saw the man, they fled from him and were greatly afraid.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The men of Israel said, “Have you seen this man who is coming up? Surely he is coming up to defy Israel. And it will be that the king will enrich the man who kills him with great riches and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7644AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7644AA\"></sup>will give him his daughter and make his father’s house free in Israel.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then David spoke to the men who were standing by him, saying, “What will be done for the man who kills this Philistine and takes away <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7645AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7645AB\"></sup>the reproach from Israel? For who is this <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7645AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7645AC\"></sup>uncircumcised Philistine, that he should <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7645AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7645AD\"></sup>taunt the armies of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7645AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7645AE\"></sup>the living God?”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The people answered him in accord with this word, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7646AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7646AF\"></sup>Thus it will be done for the man who kills him.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Now Eliab his oldest brother heard when he spoke to the men; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7647AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7647AG\"></sup>Eliab’s anger burned against David and he said, “Why have you come down? And with whom have you left those few sheep in the wilderness? I know your insolence and the wickedness of your heart; for you have come down in order to see the battle.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>But David said, “What have I done now? Was it not just a question?”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then he turned away from him to another and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7649AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7649AH\"></sup>said the same thing; and the people answered the same thing as before.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>When the words which David spoke were heard, they told <i>them</i> to Saul, and he sent for him.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>David said to Saul, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7651AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7651AI\"></sup>Let no man’s heart fail on account of him; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7651AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7651AJ\"></sup>your servant will go and fight with this Philistine.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Then Saul said to David, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7652AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7652AK\"></sup>You are not able to go against this Philistine to fight with him; for you are <i>but</i> a youth while he has been a warrior from his youth.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>But David said to Saul, “Your servant was tending his father’s sheep. When a lion or a bear came and took a lamb from the flock,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>I went out after him and attacked him, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7654AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7654AL\"></sup>rescued <i>it</i> from his mouth; and when he rose up against me, I seized <i>him</i> by his beard and struck him and killed him.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Your servant has killed both the lion and the bear; and this uncircumcised Philistine will be like one of them, since he has taunted the armies of the living God.”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And David said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7656AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7656AM\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who delivered me from the paw of the lion and from the paw of the bear, He will deliver me from the hand of this Philistine.” And Saul said to David, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7656AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7656AN\"></sup>Go, and may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> be with you.”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Then Saul clothed David with his garments and put a bronze helmet on his head, and he clothed him with armor.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>David girded his sword over his armor and tried to walk, for he had not tested <i>them</i>. So David said to Saul, “I cannot go with these, for I have not tested <i>them</i>.” And David took them off.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>He took his stick in his hand and chose for himself five smooth stones from the brook, and put them in the shepherd’s bag which he had, even in <i>his</i> pouch, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7659AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7659AO\"></sup>his sling was in his hand; and he approached the Philistine.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Then the Philistine came on and approached David, with the shield-bearer in front of him.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>When the Philistine looked and saw David, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7661AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7661AP\"></sup>he disdained him; for he was <i>but</i> a youth, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7661AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7661AQ\"></sup>ruddy, with a handsome appearance.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>The Philistine said to David, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7662AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7662AR\"></sup>Am I a dog, that you come to me with sticks?” And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7662AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7662AS\"></sup>the Philistine cursed David by his gods.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>The Philistine also said to David, “Come to me, and I will give your flesh <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7663AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7663AT\"></sup>to the birds of the sky and the beasts of the field.”",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Then David said to the Philistine, “You come to me with a sword, a spear, and a javelin, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7664AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7664AU\"></sup>but I come to you in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of hosts, the God of the armies of Israel, whom you have taunted.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>This day the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will deliver you up into my hands, and I will strike you down and remove your head from you. And I will give the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7665AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7665AV\"></sup>dead bodies of the army of the Philistines this day to the birds of the sky and the wild beasts of the earth, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7665AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7665AW\"></sup>that all the earth may know that there is a God in Israel,",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>and that all this assembly may know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7666AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7666AX\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> does not deliver by sword or by spear; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7666AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7666AY\"></sup>for the battle is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> and He will give you into our hands.”",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>Then it happened when the Philistine rose and came and drew near to meet David, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7667AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7667AZ\"></sup>David ran quickly toward the battle line to meet the Philistine.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>And David put his hand into his bag and took from it a stone and slung <i>it</i>, and struck the Philistine on his forehead. And the stone sank into his forehead, so that he fell on his face to the ground.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>Thus David prevailed over the Philistine with a sling and a stone, and he struck the Philistine and killed him; but there was no sword in David’s hand.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Then David ran and stood over the Philistine and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7670BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7670BA\"></sup>took his sword and drew it out of its sheath and killed him, and cut off his head with it. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7670BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7670BB\"></sup>When the Philistines saw that their champion was dead, they fled.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>The men of Israel and Judah arose and shouted and pursued the Philistines as far as the valley, and to the gates of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7671BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7671BC\"></sup>Ekron. And the slain Philistines lay along the way to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7671BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7671BD\"></sup>Shaaraim, even to Gath and Ekron.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>The sons of Israel returned from chasing the Philistines and plundered their camps.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>Then David took the Philistine’s head and brought it to Jerusalem, but he put his weapons in his tent.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>Now when Saul saw David going out against the Philistine, he said to Abner the commander of the army, “Abner, whose son is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7674BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7674BE\"></sup>this young man?” And Abner said, “By your life, O king, I do not know.”",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>The king said, “You inquire whose son the youth is.”",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>So when David returned from killing the Philistine, Abner took him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7676BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7676BF\"></sup>brought him before Saul with the Philistine’s head in his hand.",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>Saul said to him, “Whose son are you, young man?” And David answered, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7677BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7677BG\"></sup><i>I am</i> the son of your servant Jesse the Bethlehemite.”"
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>Now it came about when he had finished speaking to Saul, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7678A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7678A\"></sup>the soul of Jonathan was knit to the soul of David, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7678B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7678B\"></sup>Jonathan loved him as himself.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Saul took him that day and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7679C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7679C\"></sup>did not let him return to his father’s house.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7680D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7680D\"></sup>Jonathan made a covenant with David because he loved him as himself.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7681E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7681E\"></sup>Jonathan stripped himself of the robe that was on him and gave it to David, with his armor, including his sword and his bow and his belt.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So David went out wherever Saul sent him, <i>and</i> prospered; and Saul set him over the men of war. And it was pleasing in the sight of all the people and also in the sight of Saul’s servants.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>It happened as they were coming, when David returned from killing the Philistine, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7683F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7683F\"></sup>the women came out of all the cities of Israel, singing and dancing, to meet King Saul, with tambourines, with joy and with musical instruments.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The women <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7684G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7684G\"></sup>sang as they played, and said,“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7684H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7684H\"></sup>Saul has slain his thousands,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7684I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7684I\"></sup>And David his ten thousands.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Saul became very angry, for this saying displeased him; and he said, “They have ascribed to David ten thousands, but to me they have ascribed thousands. Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7685J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7685J\"></sup>what more can he have but the kingdom?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Saul looked at David with suspicion from that day on.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now it came about on the next day that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7687K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7687K\"></sup>an evil spirit from God came mightily upon Saul, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7687L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7687L\"></sup>he raved in the midst of the house, while David was playing <i>the harp</i> with his hand, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7687M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7687M\"></sup>as usual; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7687N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7687N\"></sup>a spear <i>was</i> in Saul’s hand.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7688O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7688O\"></sup>Saul hurled the spear for he thought, “I will pin David to the wall.” But David escaped from his presence twice.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7689P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7689P\"></sup>Saul was afraid of David, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7689Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7689Q\"></sup>for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with him but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7689R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7689R\"></sup>had departed from Saul.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Therefore Saul removed him from his presence and appointed him as his commander of a thousand; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7690S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7690S\"></sup>he went out and came in before the people.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>David was prospering in all his ways for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7691T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7691T\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <i>was</i> with him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When Saul saw that he was prospering greatly, he dreaded him.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7693U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7693U\"></sup>all Israel and Judah loved David, and he went out and came in before them.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Saul said to David, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7694V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7694V\"></sup>Here is my older daughter Merab; I will give her to you as a wife, only be a valiant man for me and fight <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7694W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7694W\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> battles.” For Saul thought, “My hand shall not be against him, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7694X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7694X\"></sup>let the hand of the Philistines be against him.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But David said to Saul, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7695Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7695Y\"></sup>Who am I, and what is my life <i>or</i> my father’s family in Israel, that I should be the king’s son-in-law?”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So it came about at the time when Merab, Saul’s daughter, should have been given to David, that she was given to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7696Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7696Z\"></sup>Adriel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7696AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7696AA\"></sup>the Meholathite for a wife.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7697AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7697AB\"></sup>Michal, Saul’s daughter, loved David. When they told Saul, the thing was agreeable to him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Saul thought, “I will give her to him that she may become a snare to him, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7698AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7698AC\"></sup>that the hand of the Philistines may be against him.” Therefore Saul said to David, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7698AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7698AD\"></sup>For a second time you may be my son-in-law today.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Saul commanded his servants, “Speak to David secretly, saying, ‘Behold, the king delights in you, and all his servants love you; now therefore, become the king’s son-in-law.’”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So Saul’s servants spoke these words to David. But David said, “Is it trivial in your sight to become the king’s son-in-law, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7700AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7700AE\"></sup>since I am a poor man and lightly esteemed?”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The servants of Saul reported to him according to these words <i>which</i> David spoke.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Saul then said, “Thus you shall say to David, ‘The king does not desire any <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7702AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7702AF\"></sup>dowry except a hundred foreskins of the Philistines, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7702AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7702AG\"></sup>to take vengeance on the king’s enemies.’” Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7702AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7702AH\"></sup>Saul planned to make David fall by the hand of the Philistines.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>When his servants told David these words, it pleased David to become the king’s son-in-law. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7703AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7703AI\"></sup>Before the days had expired",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>David rose up and went, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7704AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7704AJ\"></sup>he and his men, and struck down two hundred men among the Philistines. Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7704AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7704AK\"></sup>David brought their foreskins, and they gave them in full number to the king, that he might become the king’s son-in-law. So Saul gave him Michal his daughter for a wife.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>When Saul saw and knew that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with David, and <i>that</i> Michal, Saul’s daughter, loved him,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>then Saul was even more afraid of David. Thus Saul was David’s enemy continually.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then the commanders of the Philistines <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7707AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7707AL\"></sup>went out <i>to battle</i>, and it happened as often as they went out, that David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7707AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7707AM\"></sup>behaved himself more wisely than all the servants of Saul. So his name was highly esteemed."
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>Now Saul told Jonathan his son and all his servants <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7708A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7708A\"></sup>to put David to death. But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7708B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7708B\"></sup>Jonathan, Saul’s son, greatly delighted in David.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So Jonathan told David saying, “Saul my father is seeking to put you to death. Now therefore, please be on guard in the morning, and stay in a secret place and hide yourself.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>I will go out and stand beside my father in the field where you are, and I will speak with my father about you; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7710C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7710C\"></sup>if I find out anything, then I will tell you.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then Jonathan <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7711D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7711D\"></sup>spoke well of David to Saul his father and said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7711E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7711E\"></sup>Do not let the king sin against his servant David, since he has not sinned against you, and since his deeds <i>have been</i> very beneficial to you.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7712F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7712F\"></sup>he took his life in his hand and struck the Philistine, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7712G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7712G\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought about a great deliverance for all Israel; you saw <i>it</i> and rejoiced. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7712H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7712H\"></sup>Why then will you sin against innocent blood by putting David to death without a cause?”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Saul listened to the voice of Jonathan, and Saul vowed, “As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, he shall not be put to death.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then Jonathan called David, and Jonathan told him all these words. And Jonathan brought David to Saul, and he was in his presence as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7714I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7714I\"></sup>formerly.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When there was war again, David went out and fought with the Philistines and defeated them with great slaughter, so that they fled before him.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now there was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7716J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7716J\"></sup>an evil spirit from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on Saul as he was sitting in his house <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7716K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7716K\"></sup>with his spear in his hand, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7716L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7716L\"></sup>and David was playing <i>the harp</i> with <i>his</i> hand.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7717M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7717M\"></sup>Saul tried to pin David to the wall with the spear, but he slipped away out of Saul’s presence, so that he stuck the spear into the wall. And David fled and escaped that night.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7718N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7718N\"></sup>Saul sent messengers to David’s house to watch him, in order to put him to death in the morning. But Michal, David’s wife, told him, saying, “If you do not save your life tonight, tomorrow you will be put to death.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7719O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7719O\"></sup>So Michal let David down through a window, and he went out and fled and escaped.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Michal took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7720P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7720P\"></sup>the household idol and laid <i>it</i> on the bed, and put a quilt of goats’ <i>hair</i> at its head, and covered <i>it</i> with clothes.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When Saul sent messengers to take David, she said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7721Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7721Q\"></sup>He is sick.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then Saul sent messengers to see David, saying, “Bring him up to me on his bed, that I may put him to death.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When the messengers entered, behold, the household idol <i>was</i> on the bed with the quilt of goats’ <i>hair</i> at its head.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So Saul said to Michal, “Why have you deceived me like this and let my enemy go, so that he has escaped?” And Michal said to Saul, “He said to me, ‘Let me go! <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7724R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7724R\"></sup>Why should I put you to death?’”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now David fled and escaped and came <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7725S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7725S\"></sup>to Samuel at Ramah, and told him all that Saul had done to him. And he and Samuel went and stayed in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7725T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7725T\"></sup>Naioth.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>It was told Saul, saying, “Behold, David is at Naioth in Ramah.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7727U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7727U\"></sup>Saul sent messengers to take David, but when they saw <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7727V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7727V\"></sup>the company of the prophets prophesying, with Samuel standing <i>and</i> presiding over them, the Spirit of God came upon the messengers of Saul; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7727W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7727W\"></sup>they also prophesied.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When it was told Saul, he sent other messengers, and they also prophesied. So Saul sent messengers again the third time, and they also prophesied.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then he himself went to Ramah and came as far as the large well that is in Secu; and he asked and said, “Where are Samuel and David?” And <i>someone</i> said, “Behold, they are at Naioth in Ramah.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He proceeded there to Naioth in Ramah; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7730X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7730X\"></sup>the Spirit of God came upon him also, so that he went along prophesying continually until he came to Naioth in Ramah.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>He also stripped off his clothes, and he too prophesied before Samuel and lay down <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7731Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7731Y\"></sup>naked all that day and all that night. Therefore they say, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7731Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7731Z\"></sup>Is Saul also among the prophets?”"
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>Then David fled from Naioth in Ramah, and came and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7732A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7732A\"></sup>said to Jonathan, “What have I done? What is my iniquity? And what is my sin before your father, that he is seeking my life?”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He said to him, “Far from it, you shall not die. Behold, my father does nothing either great or small without disclosing it to me. So why should my father hide this thing from me? It is not so!”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Yet David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7734B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7734B\"></sup>vowed again, saying, “Your father knows well that I have found favor in your sight, and he has said, ‘Do not let Jonathan know this, or he will be grieved.’ But truly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7734C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7734C\"></sup>as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives and as your soul lives, there is hardly a step between me and death.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then Jonathan said to David, “Whatever you say, I will do for you.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So David said to Jonathan, “Behold, tomorrow is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7736D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7736D\"></sup>the new moon, and I ought <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7736E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7736E\"></sup>to sit down to eat with the king. But let me go, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7736F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7736F\"></sup>that I may hide myself in the field until the third evening.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>If your father misses me at all, then say, ‘David earnestly asked <i>leave</i> of me to run to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7737G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7737G\"></sup>Bethlehem his city, because it is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7737H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7737H\"></sup>the yearly sacrifice there for the whole family.’",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>If he says, ‘It is good,’ your servant <i>will be</i> safe; but if he is very angry, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7738I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7738I\"></sup>know that he has decided on evil.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Therefore deal kindly with your servant, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7739J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7739J\"></sup>you have brought your servant into a covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with you. But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7739K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7739K\"></sup>if there is iniquity in me, put me to death yourself; for why then should you bring me to your father?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Jonathan said, “Far be it from you! For if I should indeed learn that evil has been decided by my father to come upon you, then would I not tell you about it?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then David said to Jonathan, “Who will tell me if your father answers you harshly?”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Jonathan said to David, “Come, and let us go out into the field.” So both of them went out to the field.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Jonathan said to David, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, <i>be witness</i>! When I have sounded out my father about this time tomorrow, <i>or</i> the third day, behold, if there is good <i>feeling</i> toward David, shall I not then send to you and make it known to you?",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>If it please my father <i>to do</i> you harm, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7744L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7744L\"></sup>may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> do so to Jonathan and more also, if I do not make it known to you and send you away, that you may go in safety. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7744M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7744M\"></sup>may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> be with you as He has been with my father.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>If I am still alive, will you not show me the lovingkindness of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, that I may not die?",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7746N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7746N\"></sup>You shall not cut off your lovingkindness from my house forever, not even when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> cuts off every one of the enemies of David from the face of the earth.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So Jonathan made a <i>covenant</i> with the house of David, <i>saying</i>, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7747O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7747O\"></sup>May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> require <i>it</i> at the hands of David’s enemies.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Jonathan made David vow again because of his love for him, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7748P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7748P\"></sup>he loved him as he loved his own life.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Jonathan said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7749Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7749Q\"></sup>Tomorrow is the new moon, and you will be missed because your seat will be empty.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>When you have stayed for three days, you shall go down quickly and come to the place where you hid yourself on that eventful day, and you shall remain by the stone Ezel.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>I will shoot three arrows to the side, as though I shot at a target.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And behold, I will send the lad, <i>saying</i>, ‘Go, find the arrows.’ If I specifically say to the lad, ‘Behold, the arrows are on this side of you, get them,’ then come; for there is safety for you and no harm, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But if I say to the youth, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7753R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7753R\"></sup>Behold, the arrows are beyond you,’ go, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has sent you away.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7754S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7754S\"></sup>As for the agreement of which you and I have spoken, behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7754T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7754T\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is between you and me forever.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So David hid in the field; and when the new moon came, the king sat down to eat food.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The king sat on his seat as usual, the seat by the wall; then Jonathan rose up and Abner sat down by Saul’s side, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7756U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7756U\"></sup>David’s place was empty.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Nevertheless Saul did not speak anything that day, for he thought, “It is an accident, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7757V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7757V\"></sup>he is not clean, surely <i>he is</i> not clean.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>It came about the next day, the second <i>day</i> of the new moon, that David’s place was empty; so Saul said to Jonathan his son, “Why has the son of Jesse not come to the meal, either yesterday or today?”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Jonathan then answered Saul, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7759W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7759W\"></sup>David earnestly asked leave of me <i>to go</i> to Bethlehem,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>for he said, ‘Please let me go, since our family has a sacrifice in the city, and my brother has commanded me to attend. And now, if I have found favor in your sight, please let me get away that I may see my brothers.’ For this reason he has not come to the king’s table.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then Saul’s anger burned against Jonathan and he said to him, “You son of a perverse, rebellious woman! Do I not know that you are choosing the son of Jesse to your own shame and to the shame of your mother’s nakedness?",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>For as long as the son of Jesse lives on the earth, neither you nor your kingdom will be established. Therefore now, send and bring him to me, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7762X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7762X\"></sup>he must surely die.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>But Jonathan answered Saul his father and said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7763Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7763Y\"></sup>Why should he be put to death? What has he done?”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7764Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7764Z\"></sup>Saul hurled his spear at him to strike him down; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7764AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7764AA\"></sup>so Jonathan knew that his father had decided to put David to death.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then Jonathan arose from the table in fierce anger, and did not eat food on the second day of the new moon, for he was grieved over David because his father had dishonored him.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Now it came about in the morning that Jonathan went out into the field for the appointment with David, and a little lad <i>was</i> with him.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>He said to his lad, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7767AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7767AB\"></sup>Run, find now the arrows which I am about to shoot.” As the lad was running, he shot an arrow past him.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>When the lad reached the place of the arrow which Jonathan had shot, Jonathan called after the lad and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7768AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7768AC\"></sup>Is not the arrow beyond you?”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>And Jonathan called after the lad, “Hurry, be quick, do not stay!” And Jonathan’s lad picked up the arrow and came to his master.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>But the lad was not aware of anything; only Jonathan and David knew about the matter.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Then Jonathan gave his weapons to his lad and said to him, “Go, bring <i>them</i> to the city.”",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>When the lad was gone, David rose from the south side and fell on his face to the ground, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7772AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7772AD\"></sup>bowed three times. And they kissed each other and wept together, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7772AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7772AE\"></sup>David <i>wept</i> the more.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Jonathan said to David, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7773AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7773AF\"></sup>Go in safety, inasmuch as we have sworn to each other in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7773AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7773AG\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will be between me and you, and between my descendants and your descendants forever.’” Then he rose and departed, while Jonathan went into the city."
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span>Then David came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7774A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7774A\"></sup>Nob to Ahimelech the priest; and Ahimelech <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7774B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7774B\"></sup>came trembling to meet David and said to him, “Why are you alone and no one with you?”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>David said to Ahimelech the priest, “The king has commissioned me with a matter and has said to me, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7775C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7775C\"></sup>Let no one know anything about the matter on which I am sending you and with which I have commissioned you; and I have directed the young men to a certain place.’",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now therefore, what do you have on hand? Give me five loaves of bread, or whatever can be found.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The priest answered David and said, “There is no ordinary bread on hand, but there is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7777D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7777D\"></sup>consecrated bread; if only the young men have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7777E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7777E\"></sup>kept themselves from women.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>David answered the priest and said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7778F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7778F\"></sup>Surely women have been kept from us as previously when I set out and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7778G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7778G\"></sup>vessels of the young men were holy, though it was an ordinary journey; how much more then today will their vessels <i>be holy</i>?”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7779H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7779H\"></sup>the priest gave him consecrated <i>bread</i>; for there was no bread there but the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7779I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7779I\"></sup>bread of the Presence which was removed from before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, in order to put hot bread <i>in its place</i> when it was taken away.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now one of the servants of Saul was there that day, detained before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; and his name was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7780J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7780J\"></sup>Doeg the Edomite, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7780K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7780K\"></sup>chief of Saul’s shepherds.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>David said to Ahimelech, “Now is there not a spear or a sword on hand? For I brought neither my sword nor my weapons with me, because the king’s matter was urgent.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then the priest said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7782L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7782L\"></sup>The sword of Goliath the Philistine, whom you killed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7782M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7782M\"></sup>in the valley of Elah, behold, it is wrapped in a cloth behind the ephod; if you would take it for yourself, take <i>it</i>. For there is no other except it here.” And David said, “There is none like it; give it to me.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then David arose and fled that day from Saul, and went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7783N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7783N\"></sup>Achish king of Gath.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7784O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7784O\"></sup>servants of Achish said to him, “Is this not David the king of the land? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7784P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7784P\"></sup>Did they not sing of this one as they danced, saying,‘Saul has slain his thousands,And David his ten thousands’?”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7785Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7785Q\"></sup>took these words to heart and greatly feared Achish king of Gath.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7786R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7786R\"></sup>disguised his sanity before them, and acted insanely in their hands, and scribbled on the doors of the gate, and let his saliva run down into his beard.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then Achish said to his servants, “Behold, you see the man behaving as a madman. Why do you bring him to me?",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Do I lack madmen, that you have brought this one to act the madman in my presence? Shall this one come into my house?”"
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span>So David departed from there and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7789A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7789A\"></sup>escaped to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7789B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7789B\"></sup>the cave of Adullam; and when his brothers and all his father’s household heard <i>of it</i>, they went down there to him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Everyone who was in distress, and everyone who was in debt, and everyone who was discontented gathered to him; and he became captain over them. Now there were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7790C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7790C\"></sup>about four hundred men with him.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And David went from there to Mizpah of Moab; and he said to the king of Moab, “Please let my father and my mother come <i>and stay</i> with you until I know what God will do for me.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then he left them with the king of Moab; and they stayed with him all the time that David was in the stronghold.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7793D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7793D\"></sup>The prophet Gad said to David, “Do not stay in the stronghold; depart, and go into the land of Judah.” So David departed and went into the forest of Hereth.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Saul heard that David and the men who were with him had been discovered. Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7794E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7794E\"></sup>Saul was sitting in Gibeah, under the tamarisk tree on the height with his spear in his hand, and all his servants were standing around him.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Saul said to his servants who stood around him, “Hear now, O Benjamites! Will the son of Jesse also give to all of you fields and vineyards? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7795F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7795F\"></sup>Will he make you all commanders of thousands and commanders of hundreds?",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>For all of you have conspired against me so that there is no one who discloses to me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7796G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7796G\"></sup>when my son makes <i>a covenant</i> with the son of Jesse, and there is none of you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7796H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7796H\"></sup>who is sorry for me or discloses to me that my son has stirred up my servant against me to lie in ambush, as <i>it is</i> this day.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7797I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7797I\"></sup>Doeg the Edomite, who was standing by the servants of Saul, said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7797J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7797J\"></sup>I saw the son of Jesse coming to Nob, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7797K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7797K\"></sup>Ahimelech the son of Ahitub.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7798L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7798L\"></sup>He inquired of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7798M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7798M\"></sup>gave him provisions, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7798N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7798N\"></sup>gave him the sword of Goliath the Philistine.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then the king sent someone to summon Ahimelech the priest, the son of Ahitub, and all his father’s household, the priests who were in Nob; and all of them came to the king.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Saul said, “Listen now, son of Ahitub.” And he answered, “Here I am, my lord.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Saul then said to him, “Why have you and the son of Jesse conspired against me, in that you have given him bread and a sword and have inquired of God for him, so that he would rise up against me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7801O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7801O\"></sup>by lying in ambush as <i>it is</i> this day?”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7802P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7802P\"></sup>Then Ahimelech answered the king and said, “And who among all your servants is as faithful as David, even the king’s son-in-law, who is captain over your guard, and is honored in your house?",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Did I <i>just</i> begin <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7803Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7803Q\"></sup>to inquire of God for him today? Far be it from me! <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7803R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7803R\"></sup>Do not let the king impute anything to his servant <i>or</i> to any of the household of my father, for your servant knows nothing at all of this whole affair.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But the king said, “You shall surely die, Ahimelech, you and all your father’s household!”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7805S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7805S\"></sup>the king said to the guards who were attending him, “Turn around and put the priests of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to death, because their hand also is with David and because they knew that he was fleeing and did not reveal it to me.” But the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7805T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7805T\"></sup>servants of the king were not willing to put forth their hands to attack the priests of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then the king said to Doeg, “You turn around and attack the priests.” And Doeg the Edomite turned around and attacked the priests, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7806U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7806U\"></sup>he killed that day eighty-five men <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7806V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7806V\"></sup>who wore the linen ephod.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7807W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7807W\"></sup>he struck Nob the city of the priests with the edge of the sword, both men and women, children and infants; also oxen, donkeys, and sheep <i>he struck</i> with the edge of the sword.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7808X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7808X\"></sup>one son of Ahimelech the son of Ahitub, named Abiathar, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7808Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7808Y\"></sup>escaped and fled after David.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Abiathar told David that Saul had killed the priests of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then David said to Abiathar, “I knew on that day, when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7810Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7810Z\"></sup>Doeg the Edomite was there, that he would surely tell Saul. I have brought about <i>the death</i> of every person in your father’s household.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Stay with me; do not be afraid, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7811AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7811AA\"></sup>he who seeks my life seeks your life, for you are safe with me.”"
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span>Then they told David, saying, “Behold, the Philistines are fighting against <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7812A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7812A\"></sup>Keilah and are plundering the threshing floors.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7813B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7813B\"></sup>inquired of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying, “Shall I go and attack these Philistines?” And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to David, “Go and attack the Philistines and deliver Keilah.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But David’s men said to him, “Behold, we are afraid here in Judah. How much more then if we go to Keilah against the ranks of the Philistines?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then David inquired of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> once more. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> answered him and said, “Arise, go down to Keilah, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7815C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7815C\"></sup>I will give the Philistines into your hand.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So David and his men went to Keilah and fought with the Philistines; and he led away their livestock and struck them with a great slaughter. Thus David delivered the inhabitants of Keilah.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Now it came about, when Abiathar the son of Ahimelech <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7817D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7817D\"></sup>fled to David at Keilah, <i>that</i> he came down <i>with</i> an ephod in his hand.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When it was told Saul that David had come to Keilah, Saul said, “God has delivered him into my hand, for he shut himself in by entering a city with double gates and bars.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So Saul summoned all the people for war, to go down to Keilah to besiege David and his men.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now David knew that Saul was plotting evil against him; so he said to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7820E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7820E\"></sup>Abiathar the priest, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7820F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7820F\"></sup>Bring the ephod here.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then David said, “O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel, Your servant has heard for certain that Saul is seeking to come to Keilah to destroy the city on my account.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Will the men of Keilah surrender me into his hand? Will Saul come down just as Your servant has heard? O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel, I pray, tell Your servant.” And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “He will come down.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then David said, “Will the men of Keilah surrender me and my men into the hand of Saul?” And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7823G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7823G\"></sup>They will surrender you.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then David and his men, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7824H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7824H\"></sup>about six hundred, arose and departed from Keilah, and they went <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7824I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7824I\"></sup>wherever they could go. When it was told Saul that David had escaped from Keilah, he gave up the pursuit.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>David stayed in the wilderness in the strongholds, and remained in the hill country in the wilderness of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7825J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7825J\"></sup>Ziph. And Saul sought him every day, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7825K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7825K\"></sup>God did not deliver him into his hand.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now David became aware that Saul had come out to seek his life while David was in the wilderness of Ziph at Horesh.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And Jonathan, Saul’s son, arose and went to David at Horesh, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7827L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7827L\"></sup>encouraged him in God.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Thus he said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7828M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7828M\"></sup>Do not be afraid, because the hand of Saul my father will not find you, and you will be king over Israel and I will be next to you; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7828N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7828N\"></sup>Saul my father knows that also.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7829O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7829O\"></sup>the two of them made a covenant before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; and David stayed at Horesh while Jonathan went to his house.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7830P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7830P\"></sup>Ziphites came up to Saul at Gibeah, saying, “Is David not hiding with us in the strongholds at Horesh, on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7830Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7830Q\"></sup>the hill of Hachilah, which is on the south of Jeshimon?",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Now then, O king, come down according to all the desire of your soul to do so; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7831R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7831R\"></sup>our part <i>shall be</i> to surrender him into the king’s hand.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Saul said, “May you be blessed of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7832S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7832S\"></sup>for you have had compassion on me.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Go now, make more sure, and investigate and see his place where his haunt is, <i>and</i> who has seen him there; for I am told that he is very cunning.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So look, and learn about all the hiding places where he hides himself and return to me with certainty, and I will go with you; and if he is in the land, I will search him out among all the thousands of Judah.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then they arose and went to Ziph before Saul. Now David and his men were in the wilderness of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7835T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7835T\"></sup>Maon, in the Arabah to the south of Jeshimon.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>When Saul and his men went to seek <i>him</i>, they told David, and he came down to the rock and stayed in the wilderness of Maon. And when Saul heard <i>it</i>, he pursued David in the wilderness of Maon.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Saul went on one side of the mountain, and David and his men on the other side of the mountain; and David was hurrying to get away from Saul, for Saul and his men <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7837U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7837U\"></sup>were surrounding David and his men to seize them.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But a messenger came to Saul, saying, “Hurry and come, for the Philistines have made a raid on the land.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So Saul returned from pursuing David and went to meet the Philistines; therefore they called that place the Rock of Escape.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>David went up from there and stayed in the strongholds of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7840V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7840V\"></sup>Engedi."
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7841A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7841A\"></sup>when Saul returned from pursuing the Philistines, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7841B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7841B\"></sup>he was told, saying, “Behold, David is in the wilderness of Engedi.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7842C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7842C\"></sup>Saul took three thousand chosen men from all Israel and went to seek David and his men in front of the Rocks of the Wild Goats.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He came to the sheepfolds on the way, where there <i>was</i> a cave; and Saul <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7843D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7843D\"></sup>went in to relieve himself. Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7843E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7843E\"></sup>David and his men were sitting in the inner recesses of the cave.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The men of David said to him, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7844F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7844F\"></sup><i>this is</i> the day of which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to you, ‘Behold; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7844G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7844G\"></sup>I am about to give your enemy into your hand, and you shall do to him as it seems good to you.’” Then David arose and cut off the edge of Saul’s robe secretly.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>It came about afterward that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7845H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7845H\"></sup>David’s conscience bothered him because he had cut off the edge of Saul’s <i>robe</i>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So he said to his men, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7846I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7846I\"></sup>Far be it from me because of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that I should do this thing to my lord, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> anointed, to stretch out my hand against him, since he is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> anointed.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>David persuaded his men with <i>these</i> words and did not allow them to rise up against Saul. And Saul arose, left the cave, and went on <i>his</i> way.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now afterward David arose and went out of the cave and called after Saul, saying, “My lord the king!” And when Saul looked behind him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7848J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7848J\"></sup>David bowed with his face to the ground and prostrated himself.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>David said to Saul, “Why do you listen to the words of men, saying, ‘Behold, David seeks to harm you’?",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7850K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7850K\"></sup>Behold, this day your eyes have seen that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had given you today into my hand in the cave, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7850L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7850L\"></sup>some said to kill you, but <i>my eye</i> had pity on you; and I said, ‘I will not stretch out my hand against my lord, for he is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> anointed.’",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7851M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7851M\"></sup>my father, see! Indeed, see the edge of your robe in my hand! For in that I cut off the edge of your robe and did not kill you, know and perceive that there is no evil or rebellion in my hands, and I have not sinned against you, though you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7851N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7851N\"></sup>are lying in wait for my life to take it.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7852O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7852O\"></sup>May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> judge between you and me, and may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> avenge me on you; but my hand shall not be against you.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>As the proverb of the ancients says, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7853P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7853P\"></sup>Out of the wicked comes forth wickedness’; but my hand shall not be against you.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>After whom has the king of Israel come out? Whom are you pursuing? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7854Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7854Q\"></sup>A dead dog, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7854R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7854R\"></sup>a single flea?",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7855S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7855S\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> therefore be judge and decide between you and me; and may He see and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7855T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7855T\"></sup>plead my cause and deliver me from your hand.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When David had finished speaking these words to Saul, Saul said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7856U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7856U\"></sup>Is this your voice, my son David?” Then Saul lifted up his voice and wept.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7857V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7857V\"></sup>He said to David, “You are more righteous than I; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7857W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7857W\"></sup>you have dealt well with me, while I have dealt wickedly with you.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>You have declared today that you have done good to me, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7858X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7858X\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> delivered me into your hand and <i>yet</i> you did not kill me.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>For if a man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7859Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7859Y\"></sup>finds his enemy, will he let him go away safely? May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> therefore reward you with good in return for what you have done to me this day.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Now, behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7860Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7860Z\"></sup>I know that you will surely be king, and that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7860AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7860AA\"></sup>the kingdom of Israel will be established in your hand.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7861AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7861AB\"></sup>swear to me by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that you will not cut off my descendants after me and that you will not destroy my name from my father’s household.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>David swore to Saul. And Saul went to his home, but David and his men went up to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7862AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7862AC\"></sup>the stronghold."
		},
		"25": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">25 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7863A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7863A\"></sup>Then Samuel died; and all Israel gathered together and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7863B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7863B\"></sup>mourned for him, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7863C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7863C\"></sup>buried him at his house in Ramah. And David arose and went down to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7863D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7863D\"></sup>wilderness of Paran.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Now <i>there was</i> a man in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7864E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7864E\"></sup>Maon whose business was in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7864F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7864F\"></sup>Carmel; and the man was very rich, and he had three thousand sheep and a thousand goats. And it came about while <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7864G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7864G\"></sup>he was shearing his sheep in Carmel",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>(now the man’s name was Nabal, and his <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7865H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7865H\"></sup>wife’s name was Abigail. And the woman was intelligent and beautiful in appearance, but the man was harsh and evil in <i>his</i> dealings, and he was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7865I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7865I\"></sup>a Calebite),",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>that David heard in the wilderness that Nabal was shearing his sheep.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So David sent ten young men; and David said to the young men, “Go up to Carmel, visit Nabal and greet him in my name;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and thus you shall say, ‘Have a long life, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7868J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7868J\"></sup>peace be to you, and peace be to your house, and peace be to all that you have.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now I have heard <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7869K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7869K\"></sup>that you have shearers; now your shepherds have been with us and we have not insulted them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7869L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7869L\"></sup>nor have they missed anything all the days they were in Carmel.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Ask your young men and they will tell you. Therefore let <i>my</i> young men find favor in your eyes, for we have come on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7870M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7870M\"></sup>a festive day. Please give whatever you find at hand to your servants and to your son David.’”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When David’s young men came, they spoke to Nabal according to all these words in David’s name; then they waited.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But Nabal answered David’s servants and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7872N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7872N\"></sup>Who is David? And who is the son of Jesse? There are many servants today who are each breaking away from his master.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Shall I then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7873O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7873O\"></sup>take my bread and my water and my meat that I have slaughtered for my shearers, and give it to men whose origin I do not know?”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So David’s young men retraced their way and went back; and they came and told him according to all these words.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>David said to his men, “Each <i>of you</i> gird on his sword.” So each man girded on his sword. And David also girded on his sword, and about <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7875P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7875P\"></sup>four hundred men went up behind David while two hundred <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7875Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7875Q\"></sup>stayed with the baggage.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But one of the young men told Abigail, Nabal’s wife, saying, “Behold, David sent messengers from the wilderness to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7876R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7876R\"></sup>greet our master, and he scorned them.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Yet the men were very good to us, and we were not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7877S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7877S\"></sup>insulted, nor did we miss anything as long as we went about with them, while we were in the fields.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7878T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7878T\"></sup>They were a wall to us both by night and by day, all the time we were with them tending the sheep.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now therefore, know and consider what you should do, for evil is plotted against our master and against all his household; and he is such a worthless man that no one can speak to him.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Abigail hurried and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7880U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7880U\"></sup>took two hundred <i>loaves</i> of bread and two jugs of wine and five sheep already prepared and five measures of roasted grain and a hundred clusters of raisins and two hundred cakes of figs, and loaded <i>them</i> on donkeys.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>She said to her young men, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7881V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7881V\"></sup>Go on before me; behold, I am coming after you.” But she did not tell her husband Nabal.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>It came about as she was riding on her donkey and coming down by the hidden part of the mountain, that behold, David and his men were coming down toward her; so she met them.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Now David had said, “Surely in vain I have guarded all that this <i>man</i> has in the wilderness, so that nothing was missed of all that belonged to him; and he has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7883W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7883W\"></sup>returned me evil for good.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7884X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7884X\"></sup>May God do so to the enemies of David, and more also, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7884Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7884Y\"></sup>if by morning I leave <i>as much as</i> one male of any who belong to him.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>When Abigail saw David, she hurried and dismounted from her donkey, and fell on her face before David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7885Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7885Z\"></sup>and bowed herself to the ground.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>She fell at his feet and said, “On me alone, my lord, be the blame. And please let your maidservant speak to you, and listen to the words of your maidservant.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Please do not let my lord pay attention to this worthless man, Nabal, for as his name is, so is he. Nabal is his name and folly is with him; but I your maidservant did not see the young men of my lord whom you sent.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“Now therefore, my lord, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, and as your soul lives, since the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has restrained you from shedding blood, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7888AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7888AA\"></sup>from avenging yourself by your own hand, now then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7888AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7888AB\"></sup>let your enemies and those who seek evil against my lord, be as Nabal.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Now let <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7889AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7889AC\"></sup>this gift which your maidservant has brought to my lord be given to the young men who accompany my lord.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Please forgive <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7890AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7890AD\"></sup>the transgression of your maidservant; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7890AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7890AE\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will certainly make for my lord an enduring house, because my lord is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7890AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7890AF\"></sup>fighting the battles of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7890AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7890AG\"></sup>evil will not be found in you all your days.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Should anyone rise up to pursue you and to seek your life, then the life of my lord shall be bound in the bundle of the living with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God; but the lives of your enemies <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7891AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7891AH\"></sup>He will sling out as from the hollow of a sling.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> does for my lord according to all the good that He has spoken concerning you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7892AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7892AI\"></sup>appoints you ruler over Israel,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>this will not cause grief or a troubled heart to my lord, both by having shed blood without cause and by my lord having avenged himself. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7893AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7893AJ\"></sup>When the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> deals well with my lord, then remember your maidservant.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Then David said to Abigail, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7894AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7894AK\"></sup>Blessed be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel, who sent you this day to meet me,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>and blessed be your discernment, and blessed be you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7895AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7895AL\"></sup>who have kept me this day from bloodshed and from avenging myself by my own hand.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Nevertheless, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel lives, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7896AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7896AM\"></sup>who has restrained me from harming you, unless you had come quickly to meet me, surely there would not have been left to Nabal until the morning light <i>as much as</i> one male.”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>So David received from her hand what she had brought him and said to her, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7897AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7897AN\"></sup>Go up to your house in peace. See, I have listened to you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7897AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7897AO\"></sup>granted your request.”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Then Abigail came to Nabal, and behold, he was holding <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7898AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7898AP\"></sup>a feast in his house, like the feast of a king. And Nabal’s heart was merry within him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7898AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7898AQ\"></sup>for he was very drunk; so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7898AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7898AR\"></sup>she did not tell him anything at all until the morning light.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>But in the morning, when the wine had gone out of Nabal, his wife told him these things, and his heart died within him so that he became <i>as</i> a stone.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>About ten days later, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7900AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7900AS\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> struck Nabal and he died.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>When David heard that Nabal was dead, he said, “Blessed be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7901AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7901AT\"></sup>pleaded the cause of my reproach from the hand of Nabal and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7901AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7901AU\"></sup>has kept back His servant from evil. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has also returned the evildoing of Nabal on his own head.” Then David sent <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7901AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7901AV\"></sup>a proposal to Abigail, to take her as his wife.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>When the servants of David came to Abigail at Carmel, they spoke to her, saying, “David has sent us to you to take you as his wife.”",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>She arose <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7903AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7903AW\"></sup>and bowed with her face to the ground and said, “Behold, your maidservant is a maid <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7903AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7903AX\"></sup>to wash the feet of my lord’s servants.”",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7904AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7904AY\"></sup>Abigail quickly arose, and rode on a donkey, with her five maidens who attended her; and she followed the messengers of David and became his wife.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>David had also taken Ahinoam of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7905AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7905AZ\"></sup>Jezreel, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7905BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7905BA\"></sup>they both became his wives.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Now Saul had given <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7906BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7906BB\"></sup>Michal his daughter, David’s wife, to Palti the son of Laish, who was from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7906BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7906BC\"></sup>Gallim."
		},
		"26": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">26 </span>Then the Ziphites came to Saul at Gibeah, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7907A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7907A\"></sup>Is not David hiding on the hill of Hachilah, <i>which is</i> before Jeshimon?”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So Saul arose and went down to the wilderness of Ziph, having with him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7908B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7908B\"></sup>three thousand chosen men of Israel, to search for David in the wilderness of Ziph.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Saul camped in the hill of Hachilah, which is before Jeshimon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7909C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7909C\"></sup>beside the road, and David was staying in the wilderness. When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7909D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7909D\"></sup>he saw that Saul came after him into the wilderness,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>David sent out spies, and he knew that Saul was definitely coming.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>David then arose and came to the place where Saul had camped. And David saw the place where Saul lay, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7911E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7911E\"></sup>Abner the son of Ner, the commander of his army; and Saul was lying in the circle of the camp, and the people were camped around him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then David said to Ahimelech <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7912F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7912F\"></sup>the Hittite and to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7912G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7912G\"></sup>Abishai the son of Zeruiah, Joab’s brother, saying, “Who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7912H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7912H\"></sup>will go down with me to Saul in the camp?” And Abishai said, “I will go down with you.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So David and Abishai came to the people by night, and behold, Saul lay sleeping inside the circle of the camp with his spear stuck in the ground at his head; and Abner and the people were lying around him.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Abishai said to David, “Today God has delivered your enemy into your hand; now therefore, please let me strike him with the spear to the ground with one stroke, and I will not strike him the second time.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But David said to Abishai, “Do not destroy him, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7915I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7915I\"></sup>who can stretch out his hand against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> anointed and be without guilt?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>David also said, “As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7916J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7916J\"></sup>surely the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will strike him, or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7916K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7916K\"></sup>his day will come that he dies, or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7916L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7916L\"></sup>he will go down into battle and perish.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7917M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7917M\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> forbid that I should stretch out my hand against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> anointed; but now please take the spear that is at his head and the jug of water, and let us go.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So David took the spear and the jug of water from <i>beside</i> Saul’s head, and they went away, but no one saw or knew <i>it</i>, nor did any awake, for they were all asleep, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7918N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7918N\"></sup>a sound sleep from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had fallen on them.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then David crossed over to the other side and stood on top of the mountain at a distance <i>with</i> a large area between them.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>David called to the people and to Abner the son of Ner, saying, “Will you not answer, Abner?” Then Abner replied, “Who are you who calls to the king?”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So David said to Abner, “Are you not a man? And who is like you in Israel? Why then have you not guarded your lord the king? For one of the people came to destroy the king your lord.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>This thing that you have done is not good. As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, <i>all</i> of you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7922O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7922O\"></sup>must surely die, because you did not guard your lord, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> anointed. And now, see where the king’s spear is and the jug of water that was at his head.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Saul recognized David’s voice and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7923P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7923P\"></sup>Is this your voice, my son David?” And David said, “It is my voice, my lord the king.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He also said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7924Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7924Q\"></sup>Why then is my lord pursuing his servant? For what have I done? Or what evil is in my hand?",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now therefore, please let my lord the king listen to the words of his servant. If <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7925R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7925R\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has stirred you up against me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7925S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7925S\"></sup>let Him accept an offering; but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7925T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7925T\"></sup>if it is men, cursed are they before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7925U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7925U\"></sup>they have driven me out today so that I would have no attachment with the inheritance of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying, ‘Go, serve other gods.’",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Now then, do not let my blood fall to the ground away from the presence of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; for the king of Israel has come out to search for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7926V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7926V\"></sup>a single flea, just as one hunts a partridge in the mountains.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Saul said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7927W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7927W\"></sup>I have sinned. Return, my son David, for I will not harm you again because my life was precious in your sight this day. Behold, I have played the fool and have committed a serious error.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>David replied, “Behold the spear of the king! Now let one of the young men come over and take it.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7929X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7929X\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will repay each man <i>for</i> his righteousness and his faithfulness; for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> delivered you into <i>my</i> hand today, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7929Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7929Y\"></sup>I refused to stretch out my hand against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> anointed.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Now behold, as your life was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7930Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7930Z\"></sup>highly valued in my sight this day, so may my life be highly valued in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and may He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7930AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7930AA\"></sup>deliver me from all distress.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then Saul said to David, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7931AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7931AB\"></sup>Blessed are you, my son David; you will both accomplish much and surely prevail.” So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7931AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7931AC\"></sup>David went on his way, and Saul returned to his place."
		},
		"27": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">27 </span>Then David said to himself, “Now I will perish one day by the hand of Saul. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7932A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7932A\"></sup>There is nothing better for me than to escape into the land of the Philistines. Saul then will despair of searching for me anymore in all the territory of Israel, and I will escape from his hand.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So David arose and crossed over, he and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7933B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7933B\"></sup>the six hundred men who were with him, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7933C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7933C\"></sup>Achish the son of Maoch, king of Gath.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And David lived with Achish at Gath, he and his men, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7934D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7934D\"></sup>each with his household, <i>even</i> David with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7934E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7934E\"></sup>his two wives, Ahinoam the Jezreelitess, and Abigail the Carmelitess, Nabal’s widow.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now it was told Saul that David had fled to Gath, so he no longer searched for him.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then David said to Achish, “If now I have found favor in your sight, let them give me a place in one of the cities in the country, that I may live there; for why should your servant live in the royal city with you?”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Achish gave him Ziklag that day; therefore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7937F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7937F\"></sup>Ziklag has belonged to the kings of Judah to this day.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The number of days that David lived in the country of the Philistines was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7938G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7938G\"></sup>a year and four months.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now David and his men went up and raided <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7939H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7939H\"></sup>the Geshurites and the Girzites and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7939I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7939I\"></sup>the Amalekites; for they were the inhabitants of the land from ancient times, as you come to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7939J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7939J\"></sup>Shur even as far as the land of Egypt.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>David attacked the land and did not leave a man or a woman alive, and he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7940K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7940K\"></sup>took away the sheep, the cattle, the donkeys, the camels, and the clothing. Then he returned and came to Achish.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now Achish said, “Where have you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7941L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7941L\"></sup>made a raid today?” And David said, “Against the Negev of Judah and against the Negev of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7941M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7941M\"></sup>the Jerahmeelites and against the Negev of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7941N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7941N\"></sup>the Kenites.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>David did not leave a man or a woman alive to bring to Gath, saying, “Otherwise they will tell about us, saying, ‘So has David done and so <i>has been</i> his practice all the time he has lived in the country of the Philistines.’”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So Achish believed David, saying, “He has surely made himself odious among his people Israel; therefore he will become my servant forever.”"
		},
		"28": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">28 </span>Now it came about in those days that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7944A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7944A\"></sup>the Philistines gathered their armed camps for war, to fight against Israel. And Achish said to David, “Know assuredly that you will go out with me in the camp, you and your men.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>David said to Achish, “Very well, you shall know what your servant can do.” So Achish said to David, “Very well, I will make you my bodyguard <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7945B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7945B\"></sup>for life.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7946C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7946C\"></sup>Samuel was dead, and all Israel had lamented him and buried him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7946D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7946D\"></sup>in Ramah, his own city. And Saul had removed from the land those who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7946E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7946E\"></sup>were mediums and spiritists.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So the Philistines gathered together and came and camped <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7947F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7947F\"></sup>in Shunem; and Saul gathered all Israel together and they camped in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7947G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7947G\"></sup>Gilboa.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When Saul saw the camp of the Philistines, he was afraid and his heart trembled greatly.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7949H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7949H\"></sup>When Saul inquired of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7949I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7949I\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did not answer him, either by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7949J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7949J\"></sup>dreams or by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7949K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7949K\"></sup>Urim or by prophets.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then Saul said to his servants, “Seek for me a woman who is a medium, that I may go to her and inquire of her.” And his servants said to him, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7950L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7950L\"></sup>there is a woman who is a medium at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7950M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7950M\"></sup>En-dor.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Saul <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7951N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7951N\"></sup>disguised himself by putting on other clothes, and went, he and two men with him, and they came to the woman by night; and he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7951O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7951O\"></sup>Conjure up for me, please, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7951P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7951P\"></sup>bring up for me whom I shall name to you.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But the woman said to him, “Behold, you know <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7952Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7952Q\"></sup>what Saul has done, how he has cut off those who are mediums and spiritists from the land. Why are you then laying a snare for my life to bring about my death?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Saul vowed to her by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying, “As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, no punishment shall come upon you for this thing.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then the woman said, “Whom shall I bring up for you?” And he said, “Bring up Samuel for me.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When the woman saw Samuel, she cried out with a loud voice; and the woman spoke to Saul, saying, “Why have you deceived me? For you are Saul.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The king said to her, “Do not be afraid; but what do you see?” And the woman said to Saul, “I see a divine being coming up out of the earth.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He said to her, “What is his form?” And she said, “An old man is coming up, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7957R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7957R\"></sup>he is wrapped with a robe.” And Saul knew that it was Samuel, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7957S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7957S\"></sup>he bowed with his face to the ground and did homage.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then Samuel said to Saul, “Why have you disturbed me by bringing me up?” And Saul answered, “I am greatly distressed; for the Philistines are waging war against me, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7958T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7958T\"></sup>God has departed from me and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7958U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7958U\"></sup>no longer answers me, either through prophets or by dreams; therefore I have called you, that you may make known to me what I should do.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Samuel said, “Why then do you ask me, since the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has departed from you and has become your adversary?",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has done accordingly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7960V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7960V\"></sup>as He spoke through me; for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has torn the kingdom out of your hand and given it to your neighbor, to David.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>As <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7961W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7961W\"></sup>you did not obey the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and did not execute His fierce wrath on Amalek, so the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has done this thing to you this day.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Moreover the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will also give over Israel along with you into the hands of the Philistines, therefore tomorrow <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7962X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7962X\"></sup>you and your sons will be with me. Indeed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will give over the army of Israel into the hands of the Philistines!”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Saul immediately fell full length upon the ground and was very afraid because of the words of Samuel; also there was no strength in him, for he had eaten no food all day and all night.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The woman came to Saul and saw that he was terrified, and said to him, “Behold, your maidservant has obeyed you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7964Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7964Y\"></sup>I have taken my life in my hand and have listened to your words which you spoke to me.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So now also, please listen to the voice of your maidservant, and let me set a piece of bread before you that <i>you may</i> eat and have strength when you go on <i>your</i> way.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But he refused and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7966Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7966Z\"></sup>I will not eat.” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7966AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7966AA\"></sup>However, his servants together with the woman urged him, and he listened to them. So he arose from the ground and sat on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7966AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7966AB\"></sup>the bed.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The woman had a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7967AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7967AC\"></sup>fattened calf in the house, and she quickly slaughtered it; and she <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7967AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7967AD\"></sup>took flour, kneaded it and baked unleavened bread from it.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>She brought <i>it</i> before Saul and his servants, and they ate. Then they arose and went away that night."
		},
		"29": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">29 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7969A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7969A\"></sup>the Philistines gathered together all their armies to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7969B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7969B\"></sup>Aphek, while the Israelites were camping by the spring which is in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7969C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7969C\"></sup>Jezreel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And the lords of the Philistines were proceeding on by hundreds and by thousands, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7970D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7970D\"></sup>David and his men were proceeding on in the rear with Achish.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then the commanders of the Philistines said, “What <i>are</i> these Hebrews <i>doing here</i>?” And Achish said to the commanders of the Philistines, “Is this not David, the servant of Saul the king of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7971E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7971E\"></sup>who has been with me these days, or <i>rather</i> these years, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7971F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7971F\"></sup>I have found no fault in him from the day he deserted <i>to me</i> to this day?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But the commanders of the Philistines were angry with him, and the commanders of the Philistines said to him, “Make the man go back, that he may return <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7972G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7972G\"></sup>to his place where you have assigned him, and do not let him go down to battle with us, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7972H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7972H\"></sup>or in the battle he may become an adversary to us. For with what could this <i>man</i> make himself acceptable to his lord? <i>Would it</i> not <i>be</i> with the heads of these men?",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Is this not David, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7973I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7973I\"></sup>of whom they sing in the dances, saying,‘Saul has slain his thousands,And David his ten thousands’?”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Achish called David and said to him, “<i>As</i> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, you <i>have been</i> upright, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7974J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7974J\"></sup>your going out and your coming in with me in the army are pleasing in my sight; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7974K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7974K\"></sup>for I have not found evil in you from the day of your coming to me to this day. Nevertheless, you are not pleasing in the sight of the lords.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now therefore return and go in peace, that you may not displease the lords of the Philistines.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>David said to Achish, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7976L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7976L\"></sup>But what have I done? And what have you found in your servant from the day when I came before you to this day, that I may not go and fight against the enemies of my lord the king?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But Achish replied to David, “I know that you are pleasing in my sight, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7977M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7977M\"></sup>like an angel of God; nevertheless <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7977N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7977N\"></sup>the commanders of the Philistines have said, ‘He must not go up with us to the battle.’",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now then arise early in the morning <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7978O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7978O\"></sup>with the servants of your lord who have come with you, and as soon as you have arisen early in the morning and have light, depart.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So David arose early, he and his men, to depart in the morning to return to the land of the Philistines. And the Philistines went up to Jezreel."
		},
		"30": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">30 </span>Then it happened when David and his men came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7980A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7980A\"></sup>Ziklag on the third day, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7980B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7980B\"></sup>the Amalekites had made a raid on the Negev and on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7980C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7980C\"></sup>Ziklag, and had overthrown Ziklag and burned it with fire;",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and they took captive the women <i>and all</i> who were in it, both small and great, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7981D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7981D\"></sup>without killing anyone, and carried <i>them</i> off and went their way.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When David and his men came to the city, behold, it was burned with fire, and their wives and their sons and their daughters had been taken captive.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then David and the people who were with him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7983E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7983E\"></sup>lifted their voices and wept until there was no strength in them to weep.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7984F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7984F\"></sup>David’s two wives had been taken captive, Ahinoam the Jezreelitess and Abigail the widow of Nabal the Carmelite.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Moreover David was greatly distressed because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7985G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7985G\"></sup>the people spoke of stoning him, for all the people were embittered, each one because of his sons and his daughters. But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7985H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7985H\"></sup>David strengthened himself in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7986I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7986I\"></sup>David said to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7986J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7986J\"></sup>Abiathar the priest, the son of Ahimelech, “Please bring me the ephod.” So Abiathar brought the ephod to David.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7987K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7987K\"></sup>David inquired of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7987L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7987L\"></sup>Shall I pursue this band? Shall I overtake them?” And He said to him, “Pursue, for you will surely overtake them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7987M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7987M\"></sup>and you will surely rescue <i>all</i>.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So David went, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7988N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7988N\"></sup>he and the six hundred men who were with him, and came to the brook Besor, <i>where</i> those left behind remained.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But David pursued, he and four hundred men, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7989O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7989O\"></sup>two hundred who were too exhausted to cross the brook Besor remained <i>behind</i>.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now they found an Egyptian in the field and brought him to David, and gave him bread and he ate, and they provided him water to drink.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They gave him a piece of fig cake and two clusters of raisins, and he ate; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7991P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7991P\"></sup>then his spirit revived. For he had not eaten bread or drunk water for three days and three nights.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>David said to him, “To whom do you belong? And where are you from?” And he said, “I am a young man of Egypt, a servant of an Amalekite; and my master left me behind when I fell sick three days ago.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>We made a raid on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7993Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7993Q\"></sup>the Negev of the Cherethites, and on that which belongs to Judah, and on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7993R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7993R\"></sup>the Negev of Caleb, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7993S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7993S\"></sup>we burned Ziklag with fire.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then David said to him, “Will you bring me down to this band?” And he said, “Swear to me by God that you will not kill me or deliver me into the hands of my master, and I will bring you down to this band.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When he had brought him down, behold, they were spread over all the land, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7995T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7995T\"></sup>eating and drinking and dancing because of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7995U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7995U\"></sup>all the great spoil that they had taken from the land of the Philistines and from the land of Judah.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>David slaughtered them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7996V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7996V\"></sup>from the twilight until the evening of the next day; and not a man of them escaped, except four hundred young men who rode on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7996W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7996W\"></sup>camels and fled.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7997X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7997X\"></sup>recovered all that the Amalekites had taken, and rescued his two wives.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But nothing of theirs was missing, whether small or great, sons or daughters, spoil or anything that they had taken for themselves; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7998Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7998Y\"></sup>David brought <i>it</i> all back.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So David had captured all the sheep and the cattle <i>which the people</i> drove ahead of the <i>other</i> livestock, and they said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7999Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7999Z\"></sup>This is David’s spoil.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8000AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8000AA\"></sup>David came to the two hundred men who were too exhausted to follow David, who had also been left at the brook Besor, and they went out to meet David and to meet the people who were with him, then David approached the people and greeted them.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then all the wicked and worthless men among those who went with David said, “Because they did not go with us, we will not give them any of the spoil that we have recovered, except to every man his wife and his children, that they may lead <i>them</i> away and depart.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then David said, “You must not do so, my brothers, with what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given us, who has kept us and delivered into our hand the band that came against us.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And who will listen to you in this matter? For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8003AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8003AB\"></sup>as his share is who goes down to the battle, so shall his share be who stays by the baggage; they shall share alike.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So it has been from that day forward, that he made it a statute and an ordinance for Israel to this day.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Now when David came to Ziklag, he sent <i>some</i> of the spoil to the elders of Judah, to his friends, saying, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8005AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8005AC\"></sup>a gift for you from the spoil of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8005AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8005AD\"></sup>the enemies of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>:",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>to those who were in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8006AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8006AE\"></sup>Bethel, and to those who were in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8006AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8006AF\"></sup>Ramoth of the Negev, and to those who were in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8006AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8006AG\"></sup>Jattir,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and to those who were in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8007AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8007AH\"></sup>Aroer, and to those who were in Siphmoth, and to those who were in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8007AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8007AI\"></sup>Eshtemoa,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>and to those who were in Racal, and to those who were in the cities of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8008AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8008AJ\"></sup>the Jerahmeelites, and to those who were in the cities of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8008AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8008AK\"></sup>the Kenites,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>and to those who were in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8009AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8009AL\"></sup>Hormah, and to those who were in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8009AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8009AM\"></sup>Bor-ashan, and to those who were in Athach,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>and to those who were in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8010AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8010AN\"></sup>Hebron, and to all the places where David himself and his men were accustomed to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8010AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8010AO\"></sup>go.”"
		},
		"31": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">31 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8011A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8011A\"></sup>Now the Philistines were fighting against Israel, and the men of Israel fled from before the Philistines and fell slain <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8011B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8011B\"></sup>on Mount Gilboa.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The Philistines overtook Saul and his sons; and the Philistines killed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8012C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8012C\"></sup>Jonathan and Abinadab and Malchi-shua the sons of Saul.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8013D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8013D\"></sup>The battle went heavily against Saul, and the archers hit him; and he was badly wounded by the archers.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8014E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8014E\"></sup>Then Saul said to his armor bearer, “Draw your sword and pierce me through with it, otherwise <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8014F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8014F\"></sup>these uncircumcised will come and pierce me through and make sport of me.” But his armor bearer would not, for he was greatly afraid. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8014G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8014G\"></sup>So Saul took his sword and fell on it.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When his armor bearer saw that Saul was dead, he also fell on his sword and died with him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Thus Saul died with his three sons, his armor bearer, and all his men on that day together.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When the men of Israel who were on the other side of the valley, with those who were beyond the Jordan, saw that the men of Israel had fled and that Saul and his sons were dead, they abandoned the cities and fled; then the Philistines came and lived in them.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>It came about on the next day when the Philistines came to strip the slain, that they found Saul and his three sons fallen on Mount Gilboa.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>They cut off his head and stripped off his weapons, and sent <i>them</i> throughout the land of the Philistines, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8019H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8019H\"></sup>to carry the good news <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8019I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8019I\"></sup>to the house of their idols and to the people.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>They put his weapons in the temple of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8020J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8020J\"></sup>Ashtaroth, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8020K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8020K\"></sup>they fastened his body to the wall of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8020L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8020L\"></sup>Beth-shan.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8021M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8021M\"></sup>the inhabitants of Jabesh-gilead heard what the Philistines had done to Saul,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8022N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8022N\"></sup>all the valiant men rose and walked all night, and took the body of Saul and the bodies of his sons from the wall of Beth-shan, and they came to Jabesh and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8022O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8022O\"></sup>burned them there.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>They took their bones and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8023P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8023P\"></sup>buried them under <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8023Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8023Q\"></sup>the tamarisk tree at Jabesh, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8023R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8023R\"></sup>fasted seven days."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;